(10, 0, '第6节', '努力，便会得到', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_7461498206063.mp3', '31:18', 1878, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498206063971646.jpg', 'Sometimes they did well, but at other times their powerful human beliefs and emotions took over and clouded the way they looked at things. It made life in the maze more complicated and challenging. <br /><p>Nonetheless, Sniff, Scurry, Hem and Haw all discovered, in their own way, what they were looking for. They each found their own kind of cheese one day at the end of one of the corridors in cheese station C. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />powerful &nbsp;/''paʊə(r)f(ə)l/ &nbsp; ad. 强有力的，强大的<br />belief &nbsp;/bɪ''liːf/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 信仰，信念<br />emotion &nbsp;/ɪ''məʊʃ(ə)n/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 情绪<br />take over &nbsp;掌控，控制 &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />cloud &nbsp;/klaʊd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 云 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 使模糊，使混乱<br />complicated &nbsp;/''kɒmplɪ.keɪtɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 复杂的<br />challenging &nbsp;/''tʃælɪndʒɪŋ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 有挑战性的</p><p>nonetheless &nbsp;/nʌnðə''les/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 虽然如此，然而<br />discover &nbsp;/dɪ''skʌvə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 发现<br />in their own way &nbsp;以他们自己的方式 &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />at the end of &nbsp;在....的尽头处</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>拓展<br />one of the.... &nbsp;......的其中一个，逻辑上用于表达同类中的一个，如普通话说“你和他们一样。”，用英语可以是 You are one of them. 逻辑表示你和他们是同类，你只是这一类中的一个。</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498206063, 103, 34, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'What you wish for will come with your efforts.', '努力，便会得到。'),
(9, 0, '第5节', '头脑不宜过度复杂', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_7181498205756.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498205756325483.jpg', '<p>Like the mice, the two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, also used their ability to think and learn from their past experiences. However, they relied on their complex brains to develop more sophisticated methods of finding cheese. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />ability &nbsp;/ə''bɪləti/ &nbsp;n. 能力<br />learn from sb/sth &nbsp;向某人/某物学习<br />past &nbsp;/pæst/ &nbsp;adj. 过去的，过往的<br />experience &nbsp;/ɪk''spɪəriəns/ &nbsp;n. 经历（可数），经验（不可数），原文用复数即作为可数，所以这里理解为经历</p><p>rely &nbsp;/rɪ''laɪ/ &nbsp;v. 依赖，依靠<br />rely on sb/sth 依靠某人/某物<br />complex &nbsp;/kəm''pleks/ &nbsp; adj. 复杂的<br />develop &nbsp;/dɪ''veləp/ &nbsp;v. 发展，开发<br />sophisticated &nbsp;/sə''fɪstɪ.keɪtəd/ &nbsp;adj. 复杂的</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498205756, 102, 12, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Read on.', '继续读，不要停。'),
(8, 0, '第4节', '试错最简单', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_7251498205351.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498205351684150.jpg', 'However, for those who found their way, the Maze held secrets that let them enjoy a better life. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, used the simple trial-and-error method of finding cheese. They ran down one corridor, and if it proved empty, they turned and ran down another. They remembered the corridors that held no cheese and quickly went into new areas.<br /><p>Sniff would smell out the general direction of the cheese, using his great nose, and Scurry would race ahead. They got lost, as you might expect, went off in the wrong direction and often bumped into walls. But after a while, they found their way. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语：</strong></span><br />find one''s way &nbsp;某人找到路<br />find your way to school &nbsp;(你)找到去学校的路<br />find your way to the hospital &nbsp;(你)找到去医院的路<br />find your way home &nbsp;(你)找到回家的路<br /><br />hold /həʊld/ &nbsp;v. 握住，拿住，握有，在此故事中理解为 藏有<br />secret /''si:krit/ &nbsp;n. 秘密<br />simple &nbsp;/''simpl/ &nbsp;adj. 简单的<br />trial-and-error &nbsp;试错<br />method /''meθəd/ &nbsp;n. 方法</p><p>smell out &nbsp;闻出来<br />general &nbsp;/''dʒen(ə)rəl/ &nbsp;adj. 大致的，整体上的<br />direction &nbsp;/dɪ''rekʃ(ə)n/ &nbsp;n. 方向<br />expect &nbsp;/ɪk''spekt/ &nbsp; v. 期待，预料</p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>实用句子</strong></span></p><p>将文章的as you might expect 改成 as you expected 即是“如你所料”<br />例：As you expected, it rained so heavily.&nbsp;如你所料，果然暴雨如注。</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498205351, 101, 233, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Trial-and-error breeds the outcome.', '对的结果来自试错。'),
(3, 0, '开篇介绍+第1节', '永恒不变的是改变', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170627/vedio_3431498553137.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170627/1498529792956484.jpg', '<p><strong>本篇音频由01:55开始为第一节课</strong></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>内容简介</strong></span><br />人生犹如“迷宫”，每个人都在其中寻找各自的“奶酪”——稳定的工作、身心的健康、和谐的人际关系、甜蜜美满的爱情，或是令人充满想象的财富…… 那么，你是否正在享受你的奶酪呢？ 你又是否发现，自己的奶酪是否正在发生变化？</p><p>自本书出版以来，已经有众多读者从奶酪的故事中得到启发，从而改善了自己的事业、婚姻和生活，同时也引起了广泛的讨论。 变化总在时时发生，我们每个人都要认真思考，究竟是谁动了我的“奶酪”，我们又该如何发现新的“奶酪”？</p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>作者简介......</strong></span><br />斯宾塞·约翰逊，世界最受欢迎和最受尊敬的作家之一。作为世界顶尖企业和知名组织广泛使用的工作指南和培训工具，他的作品已经成为一种文化现象，深刻地改变了人们的生活。</p><p>斯宾塞博士善于应用生动的故事讲述现实的智慧，轻松活泼的寓言风格既让人深受鼓舞，又让人深受震撼。</p><p>他的作品《礼物》《谁动了我的奶酪》《一分钟经理人》《一分钟推销人》等长居《纽约时报》《出版家周刊》等畅销书排行榜，并被CNN、BBC、《时代》《商业周刊》《纽约时报》《读者文摘》《华尔街日报》《财富》《今日美国》等广泛报道。他的作品已经被译成41种文字全球发行，并创下销量逾亿册的惊人记录。</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>以下为第1节<br /></p><p>Once, long ago in a land far away, there lived four little characters who ran through a maze looking for cheese to nourish them and make them happy.<br /></p><p>Two were mice, named “Sniff” and “Scurry”, and two were Littlepeople—beings who were as small as mice but who looked and acted a lot like people today. Their names were “Hem” and “Haw”. <br /></p><p>Due to their small size, it would be easy not to notice what the four of them were doing. But if you looked closely enough, you could discover the most amazing things.</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px; "><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span></p><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"></blockquote><p></p><p>nourish /ˈnʌrɪʃ/ &nbsp;vt. &nbsp;滋养，抚养，使健壮<br /></p><p>sniff &nbsp;/snif/ &nbsp;v. 闻，嗅</p><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"></blockquote>scurry &nbsp;/ˈskʌri/ &nbsp;v. 急匆匆地走，跑<br /><p>being /ˈbi:ɪŋ/ &nbsp;n. 存在，本质（文中是复数形式，因为是2人）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>as small as... 像...一样小，结构是as...as... 像...一样，拓展句型：A is as small as B. A和B一样小。</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><br />look 在此意思为“看上去”，是系动词</p><p>act &nbsp;/ækt/ &nbsp;v. 行为，表现，表演</p><p>hem and haw &nbsp;犹豫不决，哼哼唧唧</p><p>due to &nbsp;由于</p><p>notice &nbsp;/ˈnəʊtɪs/ &nbsp;v. 注意，留意</p><p>discover &nbsp;/dɪˈskʌvə(r)/ &nbsp;v. 发现</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><strong>重点句型</strong></span></p><p>There + 动词，文中 There lived... 表示住着...</p><p>There be 句型只是属于此句型的其中一种情况，因为be也是动词</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1497689893, 3, 3244, 1, 0, 0, 1, 1, 'You don''t take a trip. A trip takes you.', '不是你踏上旅途，是旅途在召唤你。'),
(7, 0, '第3节', '简单与复杂的共同点', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_1841498180759.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498204340244193.jpg', 'As different as the mice and the Littlepeople were, they shared something in common: every morning, they each put on their jogging suits and running shoes, left their little homes, and raced out into the maze looking for their favorite cheese. <br /><p>The maze was a labyrinth of corridors and chambers, some containing delicious cheese. But there were also dark corners and blind alleys leading nowhere. It was an easy place for anyone to get lost. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />as different as... 如...一样的不同，在文中句首表示转折<br /><br />share &nbsp;/ʃeə/ &nbsp;v. 分享，共享，共用<br />share sth in common &nbsp;有共同点<br />put on &nbsp;穿上<br /><br />race out &nbsp;跑出去，往外跑<br /><br />favorite &nbsp;/''feɪvərɪt/ &nbsp; adj. 最喜欢的，最喜爱的<br />labyrinth &nbsp;/ˈlæbərɪnθ/ &nbsp;n. 迷宫，错综复杂<br />corridor &nbsp;/ˈkɒrɪdɔ:(r)/ &nbsp;n. 走廊，走道<br />chamber &nbsp;/ˈtʃeɪmbə(r)/ &nbsp;n. 空间，房间<br />contain &nbsp;/kənˈteɪn/ &nbsp; v. 包含，容纳<br />blind &nbsp;/blaind/ &nbsp;adj. &nbsp;盲的，瞎的，看不见的<br />alley &nbsp;/ˈæli/ &nbsp; n. 小巷，胡同</p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>重点背诵句子</strong></span><br />They shared something in common. <br />他们有共同点。<br /><br />It was an easy place for anyone to get lost. <br />这是一个对任何人来说都很容易迷路的地方。</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498180759, 99, 234, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Everything shares something with something.', '世上的一切都有共同之处。'),
(6, 0, '第2节', '简单与复杂，谁更胜一筹？', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170622/vedio_7601498127248.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498204920983751.jpg', 'Every day the mice and the Littlepeople spent time in the maze looking for their own special cheese. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, possessing simple brains and good instincts, searched for the hard nibbling cheese they liked, as mice often do.<br /><p>The two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, used their complex brains, filled with many beliefs and emotions, to search for a very different kind of cheese—with a capital C—which they believed would make them feel happy and successful. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />spend /spend/ &nbsp;v. &nbsp;花费（时间/钱）<br /><br />spend time doing &nbsp;花时间做某事<br />look for &nbsp;寻找，追寻<br />possess &nbsp;/pəˈzes/ &nbsp;v. &nbsp;拥有，占有，掌握，主宰<br />文中的possessing 属于非谓语动词的语法点，请参考语法课群的讲解<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />brain &nbsp;/brein/ &nbsp;v. 大脑，头脑<br />instinct &nbsp;/ˈɪnstɪŋkt/ &nbsp;n. 直觉，本能，天性<br />search for 搜寻，寻找<br /><br />nibble &nbsp;/''nibl/ &nbsp;v. 啃，咬<br />complex &nbsp;/kəmˈpleks/ &nbsp;adj. &nbsp;复杂的<br />fill /fil/ &nbsp;v. 充满，填满，填入<br />be filled with &nbsp;充满了...（原文为非谓语动词的被动伴随，所以没有be）<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />belief &nbsp;/bɪˈli:f/ &nbsp;n. 信仰，信念<br />emotion &nbsp;/ɪˈməʊʃn/&nbsp;&nbsp;n. 情绪，情感<br />capital &nbsp;/ˈkæpɪtl/&nbsp;&nbsp;n. 首都，资本，大写字母（文中为大写字母的意思）<br />make sb feel... 使某人感觉...</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498127248, 98, 20, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Simplicity sometimes outruns complexity.', '有时，简单远胜复杂。'),
(11, 0, '第7节', '未雨绸缪，暴雨不忧', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_1571498207287.mp3', '30:42', 1842, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498207287152511.jpg', '<p>Every morning after that, the mice and the Littlepeople dressed in their running gear and headed over to cheese station C. It wasn’t long before they each established their own routine. </p><p></p><p><strong>Sniff and Scurry continued to wake early every day and race through the Maze, always following the same route.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>When they arrived at their destination, the mice took off their running shoes, tied them together and hung them around their necks—so they could get to them quickly whenever they needed them again. Then they enjoyed the cheese. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />dress &nbsp; /dres/ &nbsp;n. 裙子 &nbsp; v. 穿，着装<br /><br />gear &nbsp; /ɡɪə(r)/ &nbsp;n. 齿轮，装置，装备<br />head &nbsp; /hed/ &nbsp; n. 头 &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 前进，往前走 <br />It wasn''t long before...... 不久之后（参考语法课2017年1月10日内容）<br />establish &nbsp; /ɪ''stæblɪʃ/ &nbsp; v. 建立<br />routine &nbsp; /ruː''tiːn/ &nbsp; n. 常规，例行程序<br /><br /><br />continue &nbsp; /kən''tɪnjuː/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 继续<br />continue to do 继续做某事<br /><br />wake &nbsp; &nbsp;/weɪk/ &nbsp; v. 醒来<br />follow &nbsp; &nbsp;/''fɒləʊ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 跟随，沿着<br />route &nbsp; &nbsp;/rut/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 路线<br /><br /><br />destination &nbsp; &nbsp;/destɪ''neɪʃ(ə)n/ &nbsp; n. 目的地<br />take off &nbsp;脱下，脱掉<br /><br />tie &nbsp; /taɪ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 系，绑<br />hung &nbsp; &nbsp;/hʌŋ/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 挂着，挂上（hang的过去式）<br />enjoy &nbsp; /ɪn''dʒɔɪ/ &nbsp; v. 享受，欣赏，享有</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498207287, 105, 56, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Precaution makes great sense when things go bad.', '未雨绸缪，暴雨不忧。'),
(12, 0, '第8节', '温水煮青蛙', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_3321498207795.mp3', '29:29', 1769, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498207795712139.jpg', '<p>In the beginning Hem and Haw also raced toward cheese station C every morning to enjoy the tasty new morsels that awaited them. But after a while, a different routine set in for the Littlepeople. </p>Hem and Haw awoke each day a little later, dressed a little slower, and walked to cheese station C. After all, they knew where the cheese was now and how to get there. <br /><p>They had no idea where the cheese came from, or who put it there. They just assumed it would be there. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />in the beginning &nbsp; 最初，一开始<br />toward &nbsp; /tə''wɔː(r)d/ &nbsp; prep. 朝向，向着<br />tasty &nbsp; /''teɪsti/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 好吃的，美味<br />morsel &nbsp; /ˈmɔː(r)s(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 少量，一小块<br />await &nbsp; /ə''weɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;vt. 等待，等候（及物动词，可直接加宾语，区别于不及物动词wait，wait一般加介词，如wait for you）<br /><br /><br />set in &nbsp;嵌入，闯入<br />after all &nbsp; 毕竟，终究<br />assume &nbsp; /ə''sjuːm/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 假设，假定，认为<span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>实用句子</strong></span><br />They had no idea. 他们不知道。<br />I have no idea. 我不知道。（日常口语，可用于替换 I don''t know.）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498207795, 106, 67, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Mind the things that are changing around you.', '注意身边时刻发生的变化。'),
(13, 0, '第9节', '得意忘形，埋下祸根', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_6991498208241.mp3', '29:27', 1767, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498208241953079.jpg', 'As soon as as Hem and Haw arrived at cheese station C each morning, they settled in and made themselves at home. They hung up their jogging suits, put away their running shoes and put on their slippers. They were becoming very comfortable now that they had found the cheese.&nbsp;<br /><p>“This is great,” Hem said, “There’s enough cheese here to last us forever.” The Littlepeople felt happy and successful, and thought they were now secure.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />as soon as &nbsp; &nbsp; 一.....就.....<br />settle &nbsp; &nbsp;/''set(ə)l/ &nbsp; v. 定居，定下来，确定&nbsp;<br />settle in &nbsp; &nbsp;在里面安定下来<br />make oneself at home &nbsp; 使自己不拘束，放松<br />suit &nbsp; &nbsp;/suːt/ &nbsp; n. 套装，一整套<br />put away &nbsp; 放到一边<br />put on &nbsp; 穿上<br />slipper &nbsp; &nbsp;/''slɪpə(r)/ &nbsp; n. 拖鞋<br /><br /><br />enough &nbsp; /ɪ''nʌf/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 足够的<br />last &nbsp; &nbsp;/læst/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. （使）持续，（使）延续<br />successful &nbsp; /sək''sesf(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 成功的<br />secure &nbsp; /sɪ''kjʊə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 安全的，有把握的<br /></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">拓展</span></strong><br />关于“成功”的各个词性与用法<br />success &nbsp; &nbsp;/sək''ses/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 成功<br />succeed &nbsp; /sək''siːd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 成功<br />succeed in doing / sth &nbsp;成功做某事，在某件事上成功<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498208242, 107, 657, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'It takes wits to refrain oneself.', '克制自己，需要智慧。'),
(14, 0, '第10节', '把奶酪据为己有', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_5601498208477.mp3', '29:25', 1765, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498208477592699.jpg', 'It wasn’t long before Hem and Haw regarded the cheese they found at cheese station C as their cheese. It was such a large store of cheese that they eventually moved their homes to be closer to it, and built a social life around it. <br />To make themselves feel more at home, Hem and Haw decorated the walls with sayings and even drew pictures of cheese around them which made them smile. One read:<br /><p>Having Cheese Makes You Happy. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />regard &nbsp; /rɪ''ɡɑː(r)d/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 看待，对待<br />regard A as B &nbsp; &nbsp;把A当作B来看待<br />store &nbsp; /stɔː(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 存储，存量<br />eventually &nbsp; /ɪ''ventʃuəli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 最后，最终<br /><br />social &nbsp; /''səʊʃ(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 社会的，社交的<br /><br />decorate &nbsp; /''dekəreɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 装饰<br />saying &nbsp; /''seɪɪŋ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 说法<br />read &nbsp;动词原形读音 /riːd/，过去式与过去分词读音 /red/（即与红色 red 同音）</p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>实用句型 </strong></span><br />It wasn''t long before sth. happened. &nbsp;不久之后某事就发生了。<br />such...that... &nbsp;如此...以致...（同 so...that...的逻辑，只是so + adj./adv.，而such + 名词/名词性词组，原文即是名词性词组）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498208477, 109, 56, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Having cheese makes you happy.', '拥有奶酪使你快乐。'),
(15, 0, '第11节', '高兴时不妨炫耀一下', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170712/vedio_1491499821776.MP3', '7:48', 468, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498208674358575.jpg', 'Sometimes Hem and Haw would take their friends by to see their pile of cheese at cheese station C, and point to it with pride, saying, “Pretty nice cheese, huh?” Sometimes they shared it with their friends and sometimes they didn’t.&nbsp;<br />“We deserve this cheese,” Hem said. “We certainly had to work long and hard enough to find it.” He picked up a nice fresh piece and ate it.&nbsp;<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />take their friends by &nbsp; 把他们的朋友带过来<br /><br />pile &nbsp; &nbsp;/paɪl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 一堆，一叠<br />point to &nbsp; 指向某人或某物<br />point at &nbsp; 对着某人或某物近距离指着（如 holding a gun pointing at someone''s head 拿着一把枪指着某人的头）<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />share &nbsp; &nbsp;/ʃeə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. &nbsp;分享，共享<br />share sth. with sb. &nbsp; 与某人分享某物<br /><br />deserve &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪˈzɜ:v/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 值得，应得（You deserve better. 你值得更好的。可用作安慰）<br /><p>have to do sth. &nbsp; &nbsp;必须做某事（含有非主动、不得不的意思）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>pick up &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />1）捡起（某物）<br />2）学起某项技能（如把英语捡起来 pick up English）<br />3）接送（如 pick up sb. at the airport）<br /><p>4）接受（信号等，如 My phone can''t pick up any signal.）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498208674, 110, 87, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'You deserve better.', '你值得更好的。'),
(16, 0, '第12节', '自信过头变自大', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170712/vedio_8081499821859.MP3', '5:36', 336, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498208844198260.jpg', 'Afterward, Hem fell asleep, as he often did. <br />Every night the Littlepeople would waddle home, full of cheese, and every morning they would confidently return for more. <br />This went on for quite some time. <br /><p>After a while Hem’s and Haw’s confidence grew into the arrogance of success. Soon they became so comfortable they didn’t even notice what was happening. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />afterward &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈɑːftə(r)wə(r)d/ &nbsp; adv. &nbsp;后来<br />fall asleep &nbsp; 入睡，睡着<br />fall - fell, &nbsp;feel - felt <br /><br />waddle &nbsp; &nbsp;/''wɒd(ə)l/ &nbsp; v. 摇摆地走<br />confidently &nbsp; &nbsp; /''kɒnfədəntlɪ/ &nbsp; adv. 有信心地，信心满满地<br /><br />quite &nbsp; &nbsp;/kwaɪt/ &nbsp; adv. 相当地，十分地<br />grow into &nbsp; 演变为<br />arrogance &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ærəɡəns/ &nbsp; n. 傲慢，自大<br />comfortable &nbsp; &nbsp;/''kʌmftəb(ə)l/ &nbsp; adj. 舒服的，舒适的</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498208845, 111, 342, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'You don''t notice what''s happening when you are so comfortable.', '当你过于舒适，你就注意不到周围在发生着什么。'),
(17, 0, '第13节', '坐吃山空', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170712/vedio_4471499821956.MP3', '6:24', 384, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498208944388217.jpg', 'As time went on, Sniff and Scurry continued their routine. They arrived early each morning and sniffed and scratched and scurried around Cheese Station C, inspecting the area to see if there had been any changes from the day before. Then they would sit down to nibble on the cheese.&nbsp;<br /><p>One morning, they arrived at Cheese Station C and discovered there was no cheese.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />as time goes on &nbsp;随着时间往前走 （原句用过去式）<br />as time goes by &nbsp;随着时间流逝<br />continue &nbsp; &nbsp;/kən''tɪnjuː/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 继续<br />scratch &nbsp; &nbsp;/skrætʃ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v.&amp;n. 划，挠，抓<br />start from scratch &nbsp; 白手起家<br />inspect &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪn''spekt/ &nbsp; v. 检查，视察，审视（原文语法点是非谓语动词的主动伴随，此语法点若不清楚可私聊海海老师讲解）<br /><br />nibble &nbsp; &nbsp;/''nɪb(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 啃咬，细咬<br />discover &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪ''skʌvə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 发现，发觉&nbsp;<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498208944, 112, 54, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Things keep changing.', '改变不停发生。'),
(18, 0, '第14节', '有备无患', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170712/vedio_5931499822011.MP3', '6:45', 405, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498209063973228.jpg', 'They weren’t surprised. Since Sniff and Scurry had noticed the supply of cheese had been getting smaller every day, they were prepared for the inevitable and knew instinctively what to do. <br /><p>They looked at each other, removed the running shoes they had tied together and hung conveniently around their necks, put them on their feet and laced them up.</p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />surprise &nbsp; /sə(r)''praɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 使意外 &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 意外<br />surprised &nbsp; /sə(r)''praɪzd/ &nbsp; adj. 感到意外的<br />supply &nbsp; /sə''plaɪ/ &nbsp; n. 供应量<br />prepare &nbsp; /prɪ''peə(r)/ &nbsp; v. 准备（原文用过去分词作为形容词，表示“准备好的”状态）<br />evitable &nbsp; /''evɪtəbl/ &nbsp; adj. 可避免的（原文加了反义前缀 in-，变成反义词，即“不可避免的”）<br />the + adj. 表示一类人或一类事物，如常见例子 the rich 泛指“富人”，the poor 泛指穷人，原文 the inevitable 意思是“那些不可避免的事”<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />instinctively &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪn''stɪŋktɪvli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 直觉地，本能地，下意识地<br />remove &nbsp; /rɪ''muːv/ &nbsp; v. 移除，移开，拿下<br />tie &nbsp; /taɪ/ &nbsp; v. 系，绑<br />hung &nbsp; /hʌŋ/ &nbsp; v. 挂（hang 的过去式和过去分词）<br />conveniently &nbsp;&nbsp;/kən''viːniəntli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 方便地<br />lace &nbsp; /leɪs/ &nbsp; v. &nbsp;用带子系，系鞋带（短语搭配&nbsp;lace up）</p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>时态</strong></span><br />had been getting smaller every day 过去完成进行时<br />完成进行时表示从过去某个时间开始到现在为止，某事一直在进行中，而原文故事基调是过去时，所以把完成进行加上过去，即过去完成进行时</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498209063, 115, 435, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Be prepared.', '时刻准备着。'),
(19, 0, '第15节', '应变而变', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_4521498209304.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498209304672920.jpg', 'The mice did not overanalyze things. <br /><p>To the mice, the problem and the answer were both simple. The situation at Cheese Station C had changed. So, Sniff and Scurry decided to change. <br /></p>They both looked out into the maze. Then Sniff lifted his nose, sniffed, and nodded to Scurry, who took off running through the maze, while Sniff followed as fast as he could. <br /><p>They were quickly off in search of new cheese. <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />analyze &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ænəlaɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 分析<br /><br />over+动词，表示“过度做某事”，原文的 overanalyze 意思是“过度分析”<br /><br />decide &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪˈsaɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 决定<br />decide to do sth. &nbsp; 决定做某事<br /><br />lift &nbsp; &nbsp;/lɪft/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 举起，抬高<br />nod &nbsp; &nbsp;/nɒd/ &nbsp; v. 点头示意<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>take off &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />1）脱掉（衣服等）<br />2）起飞<br />3）出发<br />原文为第3个意思，且用了过去式 took off<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>follow &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈfɒləʊ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 跟随，接着<br />as fast as he could &nbsp; &nbsp;尽他所能地快，根据上下文可翻译为“以最快速度地...”<br />off &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɒf/ &nbsp; prep./adj. &nbsp;离开的，落下的，在原文中可理解为“出发”<br />search &nbsp; &nbsp;/sɜ:tʃ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 搜索，搜寻，在文中作为名词，搭配结构 in search of 表示处于在搜寻的状态下<br /><br /><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p>', 1498209304, 116, 87, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Sometimes the problem and the answer are both simple.', '有时问题和答案都很简单。'),
(20, 0, '第16节', '打无准备的仗，措手不及', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_4811498209355.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498209355442821.jpg', 'Later that same day, Hem and Haw arrived at Cheese Station C. They had not been paying attention to the small changes that had been taking place each day, so they took it for granted their cheese would be there. <br />They were unprepared for what they found. <br />“What! No Cheese?” Hem yelled. He continued yelling, “No cheese? No cheese?” as though if he shouted loud enough someone would put it back. <br />“Who moved my cheese?” he hollered. <br /><p>Finally, he put his hands on his hips, his face turned red, and he screamed at the top of his voice, “It’s not fair!” <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />pay attention to sth. &nbsp; 注意，关注（某事）<br />take place &nbsp; &nbsp;发生<br />take it for granted &nbsp; &nbsp;把...当作理所当然，想当然<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />had been paying attention &nbsp;&nbsp;一直在注意（原文是否定句，即一直没注意到）<br />had been taking place &nbsp;&nbsp;一直在发生<br />二者都用过去完成进行时，对应中文可理解为“一直”<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />prepared &nbsp; &nbsp;/prɪ''peə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 准备好的（原文加了否定前缀un-，即没有准备好的）<br />what they found &nbsp; 名词性从句，表示“他们所发现的事情（东西/情况）”</p><p>yell&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/jel/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 喊叫<br />as though = as if &nbsp; 就好像... <br />shout&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/ʃaʊt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 喊叫<br />loud &nbsp; &nbsp;/laʊd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 大声得，响亮地<br />holler&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/''hɒlə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 呼喊，喊叫<br />scream&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/skriːm/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 尖叫，喊叫<br />fair &nbsp; &nbsp;/feə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 公平的<br />at the top of one''s voice &nbsp; 以某人最大音量地<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>本集内容一共出现4个表示“喊叫”的动词</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498209355, 117, 345, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Never take things for granted.', '永远不要想当然。'),
(21, 0, '第17节', '他和他的小伙伴都惊呆了', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170623/vedio_6731498209614.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170623/1498209614460536.jpg', 'Haw just shook his head in disbelief. He, too, had counted on finding cheese at Cheese Station C. He stood there for a long time, frozen with shock. He was just not ready for this. <br />Hem was yelling for something, but Haw didn’t want to hear it. He didn’t want to deal with what was facing him, so he just tuned everything out. <br />The Littlepeople’s behavior was not very attractive or productive, but it was understandable. <br /><p>Finding cheese wasn''t easy, and it meant a great deal more to the Littlepeople than just having enough of it to eat every day. Finding cheese was the Littlepeople''s way of getting what they thought they needed to be happy. They had their own ideas of what Cheese meant to them, depending on their tastes.&nbsp; <br /></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>单词&amp;短语</strong></span><br />shook &nbsp; /ʃʊk/ &nbsp; v. 摇，摇动（shake 的过去式）<br /><br />in disbelief &nbsp; &nbsp;不相信地，怀疑地<br />count on &nbsp; &nbsp;指望<br />frozen with shock &nbsp; &nbsp;惊呆了<br />deal with &nbsp; 处理<br />tune&nbsp;everything&nbsp;out &nbsp; &nbsp;把一切屏蔽<br /><br />behavior &nbsp; &nbsp;/bɪ''heɪvjə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 行为表现<br />attractive &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''træktɪv/ &nbsp; adj. 吸引人的，有吸引力的<br />productive &nbsp; &nbsp;/prə''dʌktɪv/ &nbsp; v. 有建设性的<br />understandable &nbsp; &nbsp;可被理解的（动词+后缀-able，表示可被...的） <br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>名词性从句，表示“......的东西（事情/情况等）”<br />1，第2段 what was facing him，他所面对的情况<br />2，第5段 what they thought they needed to be happy，他们认为要快乐起来所需要的东西<br />3，第5段 what Cheese meant，奶酪所意味着的东西（奶酪的意义）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498209614, 118, 43, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Nothing''s easy. That''s why you''re supposed to take it easy.', '没什么事情是轻松的，所以你才需要让自己先放松。'),
(22, 0, '第18节', '奶酪的意义', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_5701498438413.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498438413315920.jpg', 'For some, having Cheese was having material things. For others it was enjoying good health or developing a spiritual sense of well-being.&nbsp;<br />For Haw, Cheese just meant feeling safe, having a loving family someday and living in a cozy cottage on Cheddar Lane.&nbsp;<br /><p>To Hem, Cheese was becoming a Big Cheese in charge of others and owning a big house atop Camembert Hill.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br /><br />material &nbsp; &nbsp;/mə''tɪəriəl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 材料，资料，物质<br />develop &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪ''veləp/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 发展<br /><br />spiritual &nbsp; &nbsp; /''spɪrɪtʃuəl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 精神上<br /><br />sense &nbsp; &nbsp;/sens/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 感觉，意义<br />well-being &nbsp; &nbsp;生活过得好<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />For some,...... For others,......<br />对一些人来说，...... 对另外的人来说.......<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />meant &nbsp; &nbsp;/ment/ &nbsp; v. 意味着（mean 的过去式，注意读音）<br />cozy &nbsp; &nbsp;/''kəʊzi/ &nbsp; adj. 舒服的，舒适的<br />cottage &nbsp; &nbsp;/''kɒtɪdʒ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 别墅<br />Cheddar &nbsp; 一种奶酪品牌，市面常见“切达奶酪”即是<br />lane &nbsp; &nbsp;/leɪn/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 小巷，廊道<br />in charge of &nbsp; &nbsp; 把控，控制<br />own &nbsp; &nbsp;/əʊn/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 拥有<br />Camembert &nbsp; 法国一个产奶酪的村<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498438413, 119, 456, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'They knew what Cheese meant to them.', '奶酪意味着什么，他们自己知道。'),
(23, 0, '第19节', '有人原地不动，有人脚步不止', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_1301498438529.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498438529591830.jpg', 'Because Cheese was important to them, the two Little people spent a long time trying to decide what to do. All they could think of was to keep looking around Cheeseless Station C to see if the Cheese was really gone.&nbsp;<br /><p>While Sniff and Scurry had quickly moved on, Hem and Haw continued to hem and haw.</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>单词&amp;短语<br />sth. is important to sb. &nbsp; &nbsp;某事物对某人来说很重要<br />spend time doing sth. &nbsp; 花时间做某事<br />decide &nbsp; /dɪˈsaɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 决定<br />decide to do &nbsp; &nbsp;决定做某事<br />keep doing &nbsp; 保持做某事，继续做某事<br /><br />cheeseless &nbsp; /''tʃi:zləs/ &nbsp; adj. 没有奶酪的<br />由 n. + less 合成的形容词，表示没有某物的，如 moneyless 没有钱的，timeless 没有时间的，endless 没有尽头的，无穷无尽的<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />if 在原文中引导 see 的宾语从句，意思是“是否”<br /><br />gone &nbsp; /gɒn/ &nbsp; adj. 逝去的，消失的，消逝的<br />while &nbsp; &nbsp;/waɪl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;conj. &nbsp;在...期间，在...的时候<br />move on &nbsp; &nbsp;继续前进<br />hem and haw &nbsp; &nbsp;犹豫不决，等于 hesitate &nbsp;<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498438529, 120, 897, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Some say Hi while some say Bye.', '有人来，有人往。'),
(24, 0, '第20节', '奶酪没了怎么办？', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_2221498438684.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498438684297213.jpg', 'They ranted and raved at the injustice of it all. Haw started to get depressed. What would happen if the Cheese wasn''t there tomorrow? He had made future plans based on this Cheese.&nbsp;<br />The Little people couldn''t believe it. How could this have happened? No one had warned them. It wasn''t right. It was not the way things were supposed to be.&nbsp;<br />Hem and Haw went home that night hungry and discouraged. But before they left, Haw wrote on the wall:&nbsp;<br /><p>The More Important Your Cheese Is To You, The More You Want To Hold On To It.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>单词&amp;短语<br />rant and rave &nbsp; 大声叫嚷<br />injustice &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪn''dʒʌstɪs/ &nbsp; n. 非正义，不公平<br />depressed &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪ''prest/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 低沉的，沮丧的<br />be based on sth &nbsp; &nbsp;以...为基础，原文用了非谓语动词的语法点，所以没有出现 be<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />How could this have happened? 此句用了完成时 have happened，因为事情已经发生<br />warn &nbsp; &nbsp;/wɔː(r)n/ &nbsp; v. 提醒，警告<br />discouraged &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪs''kʌrɪdʒd/ &nbsp; adj. 沮丧的，泄气的<br />hold on to sth. &nbsp;紧抓住...<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498438684, 121, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'It was not the way things were supposed to be.', '事情不应该是这样的。'),
(25, 0, '第21节', '无意义的事情，重复无意义', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_2971498438797.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498438797999518.jpg', 'The next day Hem and Haw left their homes, and returned to Cheese Station C again, where they still expected, somehow, to find their Cheese.&nbsp;<br />The situation hadn''t changed, the Cheese was no longer there. The Little people didn''t know what to do. Hem and Haw just stood there, immobilized like two statues.&nbsp;<br /><p>Haw shut his eyes as tight as he could and put his hands over his ears. He just wanted to block everything out. He didn''t want to know the Cheese supply had gradually been getting smaller. He believed it had been moved all of a sudden.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>定语从句相关<br />where 在原文位置是作为定语动词的关系副词，表示主句所出现的地点作为从句发生的地点背景，它们期待在奶酪C站中找到奶酪，即“找到奶酪”这件事发生的地点背景是“奶酪C站”<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />单词&amp;短语<br />expect &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪk''spekt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v.期待，期望<br />expect to do &nbsp;期待做某事<br />somehow &nbsp; &nbsp;/''sʌmhaʊ/ &nbsp; adv. 以某种方式的，不知怎的，多少有点（表示程度）<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />no longer &nbsp; 不再（放在实义动词前如 I no longer have that. 放在be或情态动词后，如原文，再如 I will no longer see him.）<br />immobilized &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪˈməʊbəˌlaɪzd/ &nbsp; adj. 被固定不动的<br />statue &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈstætjuː/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 雕像，塑像<br />shut &nbsp; &nbsp;/ʃʌt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 闭上<br /><br />tight &nbsp; &nbsp;/taɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 紧紧的，牢固的<br />shut as tight as he could &nbsp; 尽全力紧闭双眼<br />block out &nbsp; &nbsp;阻隔，阻挡，隔绝在外，屏蔽（等于第17集中的 tune out）<br />gradually &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ɡrædʒuəli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 逐渐地，渐渐地<br />all of a sudden = suddenly &nbsp; &nbsp;突然地<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498438797, 122, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'There''s no point repeating the pointless.', '无意义的事情，重复无意义。');
INSERT INTO `lr_product` (`id`, `shop_id`, `name`, `intro`, `papers`, `thetime`, `longtime`, `user`, `price`, `photo_x`, `content`, `addtime`, `sort`, `renqi`, `type`, `del`, `del_time`, `cid`, `is_free`, `english`, `chinese`) VALUES
(26, 0, '第22节', '嘲笑无意义', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_3851498438930.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498438930119969.jpg', 'Hem analyzed the situation over and over and eventually his complicated brain with its huge belief system took hold. &quot;Why did they do this to me?&quot; he demanded. &quot;What''s really going on here?&quot;&nbsp;<br />Finally, Haw opened his eyes, looked around and said, &quot;By the way, where are Sniff and Scurry? Do you think they know something we don''t?&quot;&nbsp;<br /><p>Hem scoffed, &quot;What would they know?&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />analyze &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ænəlaɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 分析<br />over and over &nbsp; 一次又一次，反复地（也可以是 over and over again）<br />eventually &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪ''ventʃuəli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 最终，终于，= finally<br /><br />complicated &nbsp; &nbsp;/''kɒmplɪkeɪtɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 复杂的<br />brain &nbsp; &nbsp;/breɪn/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 大脑，脑力<br /><br />take hold &nbsp; 掌控，管理<br />demand &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪ''mɑːnd/ &nbsp; v. 需要，强烈要求，大声询问（原文为第3个意思）<br />by the way &nbsp; &nbsp;顺便说一声，顺便问一下<br />scoff &nbsp; &nbsp;/skɒf/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 嘲笑，嘲弄<br /><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12px;"><strong>实用口语</strong></span><br />Why did they do this to me ? 他们为什么这么对我？<br />What''s really going on here ? 这里究竟发生了什么事？<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498438930, 123, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Scoffing makes no point.', '嘲笑无意义。'),
(27, 0, '第23节', '追究到底，哲辩 or 蛮辩？', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_7461498439048.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498439048483655.jpg', 'Hem continued, &quot;They''re just mice. They just respond to what happens. We''re Little people. We''re smarter than mice. We should be able to figure this out.&quot;&nbsp;<br />&quot;I know we''re smarter,&quot; Haw said, &quot;but we don''t seem to be acting smarter at the moment. Things are changing around here, Hem. Maybe we need to change and do things differently. &quot;&nbsp;<br />&quot;Why should we change?&quot; Hem asked. &quot;We''re Little people. We''re special. This sort of thing should not happen to us. Or even if it does, we should at least get some benefits.&quot;&nbsp;<br />&quot;Why should we get benefits?&quot; Haw asked.&nbsp;<br />&quot;Because we''re entitled.&quot; Hem claimed.&nbsp;<br />&quot;Entitled to what?&quot; Haw wanted to know.&nbsp;<br />&quot;We''re entitled to our Cheese.&quot;&nbsp;<br />&quot;Why?&quot; Haw asked.&nbsp;<br />&quot;Because, we didn''t cause this problem,&quot; Hem said. &quot;Somebody else did this and we should get something out of it.&quot;&nbsp;<br />Haw suggested, &quot;Maybe we should simply stop analyzing the situation so much and go find some New Cheese?&quot;&nbsp;<br /><p>&quot;Oh no,&quot; Hem argued. &quot;I''m going to get to the bottom of this.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />respond &nbsp; &nbsp;/rɪ''spɒnd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 回应，反应<br />respond to sth. &nbsp; &nbsp; 对....作出反应<br />able &nbsp; /''eɪbl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 有能力的<br />be able to do sth. &nbsp; 有能力做某事<br />figure out &nbsp; &nbsp;解决，找出答案<br />seem to do &nbsp;看上去似乎...<br />at least &nbsp; 至少（翻译短语 at most 至多）<br />benefit &nbsp; &nbsp;/''benɪfɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 益处，利益，好处<br />entitle &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪn''taɪt(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 使符合资格，使享有权利<br />be entitled to sth. &nbsp;享有获得....的权利<br />cause &nbsp; &nbsp;/kɔːz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 引发，引起&nbsp;<br />get something out of it &nbsp; 从其中获得某些好处<br />suggest &nbsp; &nbsp;/sə''dʒest/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 提议，暗示<br />simply &nbsp; &nbsp;/''sɪmpli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 只是，简单地<br />bottom &nbsp; &nbsp;/''bɒtəm/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 底部<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用口语</span></strong><br />I''m going to get to the bottom of this. &nbsp;我要追究到底。<br />We should be able to figure this out. &nbsp;我们应该有能力解决这个问题的。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498439048, 124, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'There''s supposed to be a bottom line of everything.', '一切都应该有底线。'),
(28, 0, '第24节', '发现新大陆', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_1461498439368.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498439368390048.jpg', 'While Hem and Haw were still trying to decide what to do, Sniff and Scurry were already well on their way. They went farther into the Maze, up and down corridors, looking for Cheese in every Cheese Station they could find.&nbsp;<br />They didn''t think of anything else but finding New Cheese.&nbsp;<br />They didn''t find any for some time until they finally went into an area of the maze where they had never been before: Cheese Station N.&nbsp;<br />They squealed with delight. They found what they had been looking for: a great supply of New Cheese.&nbsp;<br /><p>They could hardly believe their eyes. It was the biggest store of cheese the mice had ever seen.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />while &nbsp; 加延续性动词，表示在.....期间<br />on their way &nbsp; &nbsp;在路上<br />on one''s way &nbsp; 表示某人在路上，如（我）在路上 on my way，英语的表达把“人”放到中间<br />farther &nbsp; &nbsp;表示物理空间距离上的“更远” &nbsp;VS &nbsp;further 表示抽象意义上的“更远”<br />up and down &nbsp; 上上下下，指找遍<br />until &nbsp; &nbsp; /ən''tɪl/ &nbsp; &nbsp; conj. 直到<br />squeal &nbsp; &nbsp;/skwiːl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 尖叫<br />delight &nbsp; &nbsp; /dɪ''laɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 高兴，愉快，乐趣<br />what they had been looking for &nbsp; &nbsp;名词性从句 表示它们一直在寻找的东西<br />hardly &nbsp; &nbsp; /''hɑː(r)dli/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adv. 几乎不<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">句型</span></strong><br />It is + 最高级 + 完成时从句 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;表示某人有史以来所做过的最....的事情<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用口语</span></strong><br />They didn''t think of anything else but finding New Cheese.&nbsp;<br />除了要找到新奶酪这件事情之外，它们什么都没去想。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498439368, 125, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Continuous efforts make a difference.', '持续的努力，总会得到回报。'),
(29, 0, '第25节', '自己一受苦便责备起别人', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_8601498439524.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498439524492102.jpg', 'In the meantime, Hem and Haw were still back in Cheese Station C evaluating their situation. They were now suffering from the effects of having no Cheese. They were becoming frustrated and angry and were blaming each other for the situation they were in.&nbsp;<br /><p>Now and then Haw thought about his mice friends, Sniff and Scurry, and wondered if they had found any Cheese yet. He believed they might be having a hard time, as running through the maze usually involved some uncertainty. But he also knew that it was likely to only last for a while.</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />in the meantime &nbsp;= at the same time, meanwhile &nbsp; &nbsp;与此同时<br />evaluate &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪ''væljueɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 评估，评价<br />suffer &nbsp; &nbsp;/''sʌfə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 遭受，蒙受<br />effect &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪ''fekt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 影响，作用，效果<br />frustrated &nbsp; &nbsp; /frʌˈstreɪtɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 沮丧的<br />blame &nbsp; &nbsp;/bleɪm/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 责怪，责备<br />blame sb. for sth. &nbsp; 把某事怪到某人头上<br />now and then &nbsp; &nbsp;偶尔<br />wonder &nbsp; &nbsp;/''wʌndə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 疑惑，想着，想知道<br />have a hard time &nbsp; &nbsp; 度过一段艰难的时期<br />involve &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪn''vɒlv/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 涉及，包含<br />certainty &nbsp; &nbsp; /''sɜː(r)t(ə)nti/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 确定性（原文加了反义前缀 un-，意思是不确定性）<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用句型</span></strong><br />It is likely to.... 很可能会.....<br />如 The city is likely to be rebuilt. &nbsp;这座城市很可能会被重建。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498439524, 126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'This, too, will pass.', '这，也会过去。'),
(30, 0, '第26节', '朦胧的觉悟', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_3271498439658.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498439658542717.jpg', 'Sometimes Haw would imagine Sniff and Scurry finding New Cheese and enjoying it. &nbsp;He thought about how good it would be for him to be out on an adventure in the maze, and to find fresh New Cheese. He could almost taste it.&nbsp;<br />The more clearly Haw saw the image of himself finding and enjoying the New Cheese, the more he saw himself leaving Cheese Station C.&nbsp;<br />&quot;Let''s go!&quot; He exclaimed, all of a sudden.&nbsp;<br />&quot;No,&quot; Hem quickly responded. &quot;I like it here. It''s comfortable. It''s what I know. Besides it''s dangerous out there.&quot;&nbsp;<br /><p>&quot;No, it isn''t,&quot; Haw argued. &quot;We''ve run through many parts of the maze before, and we can do it again.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />imagine &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪ''mædʒɪn/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 想象<br />imagine sb. doing &nbsp; 想象某人做某事<br />adventure &nbsp; &nbsp; /əd''ventʃə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 冒险，探险<br />image &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ɪmɪdʒ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 图像，影像<br /><br />exclaim &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪk''skleɪm/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 呼喊，大叫<br />respond &nbsp; &nbsp;/rɪ''spɒnd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 反应，响应，回应<br />besides &nbsp; &nbsp; /bɪ''saɪdz/ &nbsp; &nbsp; prep. 除外，表示除...外还有（在数学意义上是加），对比 except 除外（在数学意义上是减）<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用句型</span></strong><br />the more....., the more...... &nbsp;越....就越....&nbsp;<br />如本系列课程第20节 The more important your cheese is to you, the more you want to hold on to it.&nbsp;<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498439658, 127, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'When you have faith, the world makes way.', '当你有了信念，全世界都会为你让路。'),
(31, 0, '第27节', '无冒险，不收获', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_2311498439928.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498439928472141.jpg', '&quot;I''m getting too old for that,&quot; Hem said. &quot;And I''m afraid I''m not interested in getting lost and making a fool of myself. Are you?&quot;&nbsp;<br />With that, Haw''s fear of failing returned and his hope of finding New Cheese faded.&nbsp;<br /><p>So every day, the Little people continued to do what they had done before. They went to Cheese Station C, found no Cheese, and returned home, carrying their worries and frustrations with them.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />too old for sth. &nbsp;太老了以致于做不了某事<br />be interested in sth. &nbsp;对某事物感兴趣<br />get lost &nbsp; 迷路，迷失<br />make a fool of sb. &nbsp;使某人出丑<br /><br />fade &nbsp; &nbsp;/feɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 消退，消散，褪色<br />carry &nbsp; &nbsp;/''kæri/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 搬运，带有（原文 carrying 表示伴随，理解为 带着）<br />worry &nbsp; &nbsp;/''wʌri/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 担心，焦虑<br />frustration &nbsp; &nbsp;/frʌ''streɪʃ(ə)n/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 沮丧<br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />实用句子</span></strong><br />I''m getting too old for that. 我越来越老了，做不了那样的事。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498439928, 128, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Nothing ventured, nothing gained.', '无冒险，不收获。'),
(32, 0, '第28节', '过头的自我安慰', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_8851498440055.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498440055667964.jpg', 'They tried to deny what was happening, but found it harder to get to sleep, had less energy the next day, and were becoming irritable.&nbsp;<br />Their homes were not the nurturing places they once were. The Little people had difficulty sleeping and were having nightmares about not finding any Cheese.&nbsp;<br />But Hem and Haw still returned to Cheese Station C and waited there every day.&nbsp;<br /><p>Hem said, &quot;You know if we just work harder we''ll find that nothing has really changed that much. The Cheese is probably nearby. Maybe they just hid it behind the wall.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />try to do &nbsp; 努力去做某事<br />deny &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪ''naɪ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 否认<br />find it adj. to do &nbsp; &nbsp;发现做某事是......的<br />irritable &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ɪrɪtəb(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 易怒的，暴躁的<br /><br />nurture &nbsp; &nbsp;/''nɜː(r)tʃə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 滋养，养育（原文加 ing，变成形容词，表示“滋养人的”）<br />have difficulty doing &nbsp; &nbsp;做某事有困难<br />nightmare &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈnaɪtˌmeə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 恶梦<br /><br />that much &nbsp; &nbsp;那么多，那样地多（表示程度）<br />probably &nbsp; &nbsp;/''prɒbəbli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 很可能地<br />hide &nbsp; &nbsp;/haɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 隐藏（原文用的是过去式 hid）<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498440055, 129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Never be self-deceiving.', '不要自欺。'),
(33, 0, '第29节', '这场自欺更彻底', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_6811498440331.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498440331761172.jpg', 'The next day, Hem and Haw returned with tools. Hem held the chisel, while Haw banged on the hammer until they made a hole in the wall of Cheese Station C. They peered inside but found no Cheese.&nbsp;<br />They were disappointed but believed they could solve the problem. So they started earlier, stayed longer, and worked harder. But after a while, all they had was a large hole in the wall.&nbsp;<br />Haw was beginning to realize the difference between activity and productivity.&nbsp;<br />&quot;Maybe,&quot; Hem said, &quot;we should just sit here and see what happens. Sooner or later they have to put the Cheese back.&quot;&nbsp;<br /><p>Haw wanted to believe that. So each day he went home to rest and returned reluctantly with Hem to Cheese Station C. But Cheese never reappeared.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />tool &nbsp; &nbsp;/tuːl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 工具，器材<br />chisel &nbsp; &nbsp;/''tʃɪz(ə)l/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 凿子<br />bang &nbsp; &nbsp;/bæŋ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 猛敲，猛击<br />hammer &nbsp; &nbsp;/''hæmə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 锤子，铁锤<br />peer &nbsp; &nbsp;/pɪə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 窥视 &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 同龄人，同行<br /><br />disappointed &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪsə''pɔɪntɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 失望的<br />solve &nbsp; &nbsp;/sɒlv/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 解决 &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />solve the problem &nbsp; 解决这个问题<br />realize &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈriəˌlaɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 意识到，了解，实现<br />difference &nbsp; &nbsp;/''dɪfrəns/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 区别，不同<br />the difference between A and B &nbsp; A和B之间的区别</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />activity &nbsp; &nbsp;/æk''tɪvəti/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 活动，劳动<br />productivity &nbsp; &nbsp;/prɒdʌk''tɪvəti/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 生产力，产能，产出<br /><br />sooner or later &nbsp; &nbsp;迟早 &nbsp;<br />reluctantly &nbsp; &nbsp; /rɪ''lʌktəntli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 勉强地，不情愿地<br />appear &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''pɪə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 出现（动词加前缀 re-，表示再做一次，原文即是一个例子，reappear 重现，再现）<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用口语</span></strong><br />Let''s see what happens. &nbsp;让我们看看情况（会如何）。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498440331, 130, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Go and see.', '走着瞧。'),
(34, 0, '第30节', '再次觉悟', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_4841498441232.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498441232847298.jpg', 'By now the Little people were growing weak from hunger and stress. Haw was getting tired of just waiting for their &nbsp;situation to improve. He began to see that the longer they stayed in their Cheeseless situation, the worse off they would be.&nbsp;<br />Haw knew they were losing their edge.&nbsp;<br /><p>Finally, one day Haw began laughing at himself. &quot;Haw, haw, look at us. We keep doing the same things over and over again and wonder why things don''t get better. If this wasn''t so ridiculous, it would be even funnier.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />by now &nbsp; 到目前为止<br />grow &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɡrəʊ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v.生长，演变<br />weak &nbsp; &nbsp;/wiːk/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 虚弱的<br />get tired of &nbsp; &nbsp;对.....变得厌倦（原文用进行时 getting）<br />situation &nbsp; &nbsp;/sɪtʃu''eɪʃ(ə)n/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 场景，情景，境况<br />improve &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪm''pruːv/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 提高，改善<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />be well off &nbsp; 生活得好<br />be badly off &nbsp; 生活得不好（原文用比较级 worse off）<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />edge &nbsp; &nbsp;/edʒ/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 边缘，刀刃，利刃，优势（原文为第4个意思）<br />begin doing &nbsp; &nbsp;开始做某事<br />laugh at sb. &nbsp; 嘲笑某人<br />keep doing &nbsp; &nbsp;保持做某事的状态，持续地做<br />over and over again &nbsp; &nbsp;一次又一次，反复<br />wonder &nbsp; &nbsp; /''wʌndə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 惊讶，感到奇怪，想知道<br />ridiculous &nbsp; &nbsp; /rɪ''dɪkjʊləs/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 可笑的，滑稽的，荒唐的<br /><br />funny &nbsp; &nbsp;/''fʌni/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 可笑的，滑稽的<br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />实用句型</span></strong><br />the + 比较级，the + 比较级 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 越....，就越....<br />如，The more exercise you do, the stronger you will be. &nbsp;锻炼得越多，你就会越强壮。<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498441232, 131, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'If this wasn''t so ridiculous, it would be even funnier.', '如果这都不算好笑，那就更好笑了。'),
(35, 0, '第31节', '觉悟之后，开始行动', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_5291498441642.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498441642392606.jpg', 'Haw did not like the idea of having to run through the maze again, because he knew he would get lost and have no idea where he would find any Cheese. But he had to laugh at his folly when he saw what his fear was doing to him.&nbsp;<br />He asked Hem, &quot;Where did we put our running shoes?&quot; It took a long time to find them because they had put everything away when they found their Cheese at Cheese Station C, thinking they wouldn''t be needing them anymore.&nbsp;<br /><p>As Hem saw his friend getting into his running gear, he said, &quot;You''re not really going out into the maze again, are you? Why don''t you just wait here with me until they put the Cheese back?&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />get lost &nbsp; &nbsp;迷路，迷失<br />have no idea &nbsp; &nbsp;没主意，不知道<br />laugh at &nbsp; &nbsp; 嘲笑<br />folly &nbsp; &nbsp;/''fɒli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 愚蠢的行为、举动<br />put everything away &nbsp; &nbsp;把一切都放起来了（放到一边）<br />thinking &nbsp;在文中是非谓语动词的主动伴随，表示“（同时在）想着...”，可参考【海海English】语法课的讲解<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用句型</span></strong><br />1，It takes some time to do sth. &nbsp;做某事需要花某时长<br />原文用过去式 It took a long time to find them. 花了很长时间才找到它们。<br /><br />2，反义疑问句<br />结构：陈述句，反义疑问？<br />对应中文的“该不是......吧？”，或“......, 不是吗？”<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498441642, 132, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'It takes time.', '那需要时间。'),
(36, 0, '第32节', '昨天的Cheese回不来', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_1681498441764.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498441764892462.jpg', '&quot;Because, you just don''t get it.&quot; Haw said. &quot;I didn''t want to see it either, but now I realize they''re never going to put yesterday''s Cheese back. It''s time to find New Cheese.&quot;&nbsp;<br />Hem argued, &quot;But what if there''s no Cheese out there? Or even if there is, what if you don''t find it?&quot;&nbsp;<br />&quot;I don''t know,&quot; Haw said. He had asked himself those same questions too many times and felt the fears again that kept him where he was.&nbsp;<br />He asked himself, &quot;Where am I more likely to find Cheese—here or in the maze?&quot;&nbsp;<br /><p>He painted a picture in his mind. He saw himself venturing out into the maze with a smile on his face.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />either &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈi:ðɚ/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adv. 也不（用于否定句）<br />where he was &nbsp; &nbsp;从句表达一个地点，意为“他所在的那个地方”<br />be likely to do sth. &nbsp; &nbsp;可能做某事<br />paint &nbsp; &nbsp;/peɪnt/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 绘画，画出<br />venture &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈventʃə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 冒险<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用句型</span></strong><br />It''s time to do sth. &nbsp; &nbsp; 是时候做某事了<br />What if + 陈述句？ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;如果......怎么办？<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498441764, 133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'What has left me is yesterday that never comes back.', '弃我去者，昨日之日不可留。'),
(37, 0, '第33节', '想象美好，会带你走向美好', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_8871498441891.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498441891714561.jpg', 'While this picture surprised him, it made him feel good. He saw himself getting lost now and then in the maze, but felt confident he would eventually find New Cheese out there and all the good things that came with it. He gathered his courage.&nbsp;<br />Then he used his imagination to paint the most believable picture he could — with the most realistic details — of him finding and enjoying the taste of New Cheese.&nbsp;<br />He saw himself eating Swiss cheese with holes in it, bright orange Cheddar and American cheeses, Italian Mozzarella and wonderfully soft French Camembert Cheese, and......&nbsp;<br />Then he heard Hem say something and realized they were still at Cheese Station C.&nbsp;<br /><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />surprise &nbsp; &nbsp;/səˈpraɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 使惊讶，使意外<br />see sb. doing &nbsp; &nbsp; 看到某人在做某事<br />get lost &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;迷失，迷路<br />now and then &nbsp; &nbsp; 偶尔<br />eventually &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪˈventʃuəli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adv. 最后，最终<br />come with it &nbsp; &nbsp;随之而来<br />gather &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈgæðə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 聚集，积聚<br />courage &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈkʌrɪdʒ/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 勇气，胆量<br />gather courage &nbsp; &nbsp;鼓起勇气<br /><br />imagination &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪˌmædʒɪˈneɪʃn/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 想象，想象力<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />believable &nbsp; &nbsp; /bɪˈli:vəbl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 可信的（动词加后缀 -able，变成adj. 表示“可被......的”，原文是 believe “相信” 加了 -able，变成 believable “可被相信的”）</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />realistic &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˌri:əˈlɪstɪk/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 真实的，真切的<br />detail &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈdi:teɪl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 细节<br /><br />Swiss &nbsp; &nbsp;/swɪs/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 瑞士人 &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 瑞士的<br />Cheddar &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈtʃedə/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 一种奶酪的牌子，译“切达”或“车达”<br /><br />Mozzarella &nbsp; &nbsp; 意大利的一种奶酪牌子<br />realize &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈri:əlaɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 意识到，了解到<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498441891, 134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Imagination leads you.', '想象美好，会带你走向美好。'),
(38, 0, '第34节', '生活在向前走，我们也该如此', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_8501498442166.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498442166631512.jpg', 'Haw said,&quot; Sometimes, Hem, things change and they are never the same again. This looks like one of those times. That''s life! Life moves on. And so should we.&quot;&nbsp;<br />Haw looked at his emaciated companion and tried to talk sense to him, but Hem''s fear had turned into anger and he wouldn''t listen.&nbsp;<br />Haw didn''t mean to be rude to his friend, but he had to laugh at how silly they both looked.&nbsp;<br /><p>As Haw prepared to leave, he started to feel more alive, knowing that he was finally able to laugh at himself, let go and move on.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />So should we. &nbsp;倒装句，意为“我们也应该如此。” &nbsp;So 所指代的是上文所说的情况。<br />emaciated &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɪˈmeɪʃieɪtɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 瘦削的，瘦弱的<br />companion &nbsp; &nbsp;/kəmˈpæniən/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 同伴<br />talk sense to sb. &nbsp; &nbsp;与某人讲道理<br />turn into &nbsp; &nbsp; 转变，变成<br /><br /><br />anger &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈæŋgə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 生气，愤怒，怒气<br /><br />mean to do &nbsp; &nbsp;故意做某事<br />rude &nbsp; &nbsp;/ru:d/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 粗鲁的，粗暴的&nbsp;<br />laugh at &nbsp; &nbsp;嘲笑<br />silly &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈsɪli/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 愚蠢的<br />alive &nbsp; &nbsp;/əˈlaɪv/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 活着的，有生气的<br /><br /><br />let go &nbsp; 放手，放开（若后面搭配放开的对象，则加of，let go of sth.）<br />move on &nbsp; &nbsp; 继续前进<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498442166, 135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'You have to put the past behind you before you can move on.', '放下过去，才能更好地前进。'),
(39, 0, '第35节', '应变而不变，最后只会走投无路', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_6051498442461.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498442461628838.jpg', 'Haw laughed and announced, &quot;It''s...Maze...time!&quot;&nbsp;<br />Hem didn''t laugh and he didn''t respond.&nbsp;<br />Haw picked up and small, sharp rock and wrote a serious thought on the wall for Hem to think about. As was his custom, Haw even drew a picture of Cheese around it, hoping it would help Hem to smile, lighten up, and go after the New Cheese. But Hem didn''t want to see it.&nbsp;<br />It read:&nbsp;<br /><p>If You Do Not Change, You Can Become Extinct.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p>单词&amp;短语<br />announce &nbsp; &nbsp;/əˈnaʊns/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 宣布，公布<br />respond &nbsp; 见 Cheese 23<br />pick up &nbsp;见 Cheese 11<br />serious &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈsɪəriəs/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 严肃的，认真的<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />As was his custom &nbsp;前置的定语从句，表示“如他往常的习惯”<br />lighten up &nbsp; &nbsp;点亮，启迪<br />go after &nbsp; &nbsp; 追寻，追求<br />extinct &nbsp; &nbsp; /ɪkˈstɪŋkt/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 灭绝的，在原文中可理解为“走投无路”<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498442461, 136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'If you do not change, you can become extinct.', '应变而不变，最后只会走投无路。'),
(40, 0, '第36节', '蜕变之后', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_6161498442663.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498442663233653.jpg', 'Then, Haw stuck his head out and peered anxiously into the maze. He thought about how he''d gotten himself into this cheeseless situation.&nbsp;<br />He had believed that there may not be any Cheese in the maze, or he may not find it. Such fearful beliefs were immobilizing and killing him.&nbsp;<br /><p>Haw smiled. He knew Hem was wondering, &quot;Who moved my cheese?&quot; But Haw was wondering, &quot;Why didn''t I get up and move with the Cheese sooner?&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />stick out &nbsp; &nbsp;伸出去，探出去（原文为过去式，stuck out）<br />peer &nbsp; &nbsp;/pɪə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 窥视，凝视，盯着看<br />anxiously &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈæŋkʃəs/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 焦急的，焦虑的（原文是副词形式 anxiously 焦急地）<br />get sb. into... 使某人进入/陷入.....<br />fearful &nbsp; &nbsp; /ˈfɪəfl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 可怕的，吓人的<br />belief &nbsp; &nbsp;/bɪˈli:f/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 信念，想法<br />immobilize &nbsp; &nbsp; /ɪˈməʊbəlaɪz/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 使固定不动<br />kill &nbsp; &nbsp; /kɪl/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 杀死<br />sooner &nbsp; &nbsp; /''su:nə/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adv. 早一些，快一些<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">实用句型</span></strong><br />I was wondering...... 我在想.....&nbsp;<br />如：I was wondering if you could help me. 我在想你是否能帮帮我。<br />Why didn''t I..... 我为什么没有（做某事）呢？<br />如：原文句子<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498442663, 137, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Why didn''t I see it earlier?', '为什么我没有早点想明白呢？'),
(41, 0, '第37节', '假如没有恐惧，你会怎么做？', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_6641498443061.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498443061532426.jpg', 'As he started out into the maze, Haw looked back to where he had come from and felt its comfort. He could feel himself being drawn back into familiar territory — even though he hadn''t found Cheese here for some time.&nbsp;<br />Haw became more anxious and wondered if he really wanted to go out into the maze. He wrote a saying on the wall ahead of him and stared at it for some time:&nbsp;<br /><p>What Would You Do If You Weren''t Afraid?&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />look back &nbsp; &nbsp; 回头看<br /><br />comfort &nbsp; &nbsp; /''kʌmfə(r)t/ &nbsp; &nbsp;n. 安慰<br />draw back &nbsp; &nbsp;往回拉（原文是被动语态，用过去分词 drawn）<br />familiar &nbsp; &nbsp; /fə''mɪliə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 熟悉的，常见到的<br />territory &nbsp; &nbsp;/''terət(ə)ri/ &nbsp; &nbsp; n. 领土，领地，地盘，区域<br />even though &nbsp; &nbsp; 即使，即便（表让步）<br /><br />anxious &nbsp; &nbsp; /''æŋkʃəs/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 焦急的，焦虑的<br />ahead of him &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;在他前面<br />stare &nbsp; &nbsp; /steə(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp; v. 凝视，盯着看<br />stare at sb./sth. &nbsp; &nbsp;盯着某人/某物看<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498443062, 138, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Fear results from the unknown.', '恐惧来自未知。'),
(42, 0, '第38节', '深呼吸，然后勇闯未知', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_8251498443244.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498443244352476.jpg', 'He thought about it. He knew sometimes some fear can be good. When you are afraid things are going to get worse if you don''t do something, it can prompt you into action. But it is not good when you are so afraid that it keeps you from doing anything.&nbsp;<br />He looked to his right, to the part of the maze where he had never been, and felt the fear.&nbsp;<br /><p>Then, he took a deep breath, turned right into the maze, and jogged slowly, into the unknown.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />afraid &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''freɪd/ &nbsp; &nbsp; adj. 害怕的，担心（某事会发生）<br />get worse &nbsp; &nbsp;变差，变化，恶化（worse 是多数表示负面意义的词的比较级，意为 更糟）<br />prompt sb. into action &nbsp; &nbsp;促使某人行动起来<br />keep sb. from doing &nbsp; &nbsp;阻止某人做某事，让某人做不了某事<br /><br />take a deep breath &nbsp; &nbsp; 深呼吸<br />the unknown &nbsp; &nbsp; 未知的一切<br /></p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1498443244, 139, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Take a deep breath.', '深呼吸。'),
(43, 0, '第39节', '迟到好过不到', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170626/vedio_7771498443502.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170626/1498443502575295.jpg', 'As he tried to find his way, Haw worried, at first, that he might have waited too long in Cheese Station C. He hadn''t had any cheese for so long that he was now weak. It took him longer and it was more painful than usual to get through the maze.&nbsp;<br />He decided that if he ever got the chance again, he would get out of his comfort zone and adapt to change sooner. It would make things easier.&nbsp;<br /><p>Then, Haw smiled a weak smile as he thought, &quot;Better late than never.&quot;</p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style="font-size:12px;">单词&amp;短语</span></strong><br />at first &nbsp; &nbsp;最初，一开始<br />might have done &nbsp; &nbsp;可能已经做了某事<br />so......that...... &nbsp; 如此....以致于...（发生了某个结果）<br />It takes sb. some time to do &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;做某事花了某人某时间<br />comfort zone &nbsp; &nbsp;舒适区<br />adapt to... &nbsp; 适应....&nbsp;<br /><br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1498443502, 140, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Better late than never.', '迟到好过不到。'),
(46, 0, '第42节', '回头想想，恍然大悟', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170717/vedio_8351500254964.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170717/1500254964761129.png', '<p><strong>Later, as Haw looked back on things, he realized that the Cheese at Cheese Station C had not just disappeared overnight, as he had once believed. The amount of Cheese that had been there toward the end had been getting smaller, and what was left had grown old. It didn’t taste as good. </strong></p><p><strong>Mold may even have begun to grow on the old Cheese, although he hadn’t noticed it. He had to admit, however, that if he had wanted to, he probably could have seen what was coming. But he didn’t. </strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />单词&amp;短语<br />look back on 回顾<br />realize &nbsp; /ˈriəˌlaɪz/ &nbsp; v. 意识到<br />disappear &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪsəˈpɪə(r)/ &nbsp;v. 消失<br />overnight &nbsp;由over和night两个词组成的合成词，意思是“一夜之间” ，也可拓展理解为“突然之间”</strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />amount &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''maʊnt/ &nbsp; n. 数量<br />amount 加不可数名词，而number 加可数名词<br />toward &nbsp; &nbsp;/tə''wɔː(r)d/ &nbsp; &nbsp;prep. 朝着，朝向<br />left &nbsp; &nbsp;/left/ &nbsp; v. 在文中是 leave 的过去分词，意思是“留下的 ，剩下的”<br />mold &nbsp; &nbsp;/məʊld/ &nbsp; n. 霉菌<br />although &nbsp; &nbsp;/ɔːl''ðəʊ/ &nbsp; conj. 虽然，即使<br />notice &nbsp; &nbsp;/''nəʊtɪs/ &nbsp; v. 注意到<br />had to admit &nbsp; 不得不承认<br />probably &nbsp; &nbsp;/''prɒbəbli/ &nbsp; adv. 很可能地<br />could have done &nbsp; 本可以做某事<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />过去虚拟结构：If I had done, I would/could/should have done</strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></p>', 1500254964, 143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'There''s always something that you only become conscious of in retrospect.', '总有些事情，后知后觉。'),
(44, 0, '第40节', '走两步，退一步', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170709/vedio_7131499586483.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170709/1499586483992563.jpg', '<p><strong>During the next several days, Haw found a little Cheese here and there, but nothing that lasted very long. He had hoped to find enough Cheese to take some back to Hem and encourage him to come out into the Maze. </strong></p><p><strong>But Haw didn''t feel confident enough yet. He had to admit he found it confusing in the Maze. Things seemed to have changed since the last time he was out here. </strong></p><p><strong>Just when he thought he was getting ahead, he would get lost in the corridors. It seemed his progress was two steps forward and one step backward. It was a challenge, but he had to admit that being back in the Maze, hunting for Cheese, wasn''t nearly as bad as he feared it might be.</strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></p><p><strong>单词&amp;短语<br />during &nbsp; /ˈdjʊərɪŋ/ &nbsp;prep. &nbsp;在....期间<br />several &nbsp; /ˈsevrəl/ &nbsp; adj. &nbsp;几个的，一些的<br />here and there &nbsp; 到处，四处<br />last &nbsp; /læst/ &nbsp; v. 持续，持久<br />encourage &nbsp; /ɪnˈkʌrɪdʒ/ &nbsp; v. 鼓励<br />encourage sb. to do &nbsp;鼓励某人去做某事<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />admit &nbsp; /ədˈmɪt/ &nbsp; v. 承认，允许<br />find it + adj. &nbsp;发现某事物是....的（其中it是形式宾语，无需翻译）<br />seem &nbsp; /si:m/ &nbsp; v. 看上去似乎....<br />seem to do &nbsp; 看上去似乎要做某事（或发生某事）<br /><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />get ahead &nbsp; 往前进<br />get lost &nbsp; 迷路，迷失<br />progress &nbsp; /ˈprɑ:gres/ &nbsp; n. 进步，进程，进展<br />forward &nbsp; /ˈfɔ:wəd/ &nbsp;adv. 向前<br />backward &nbsp; /ˈbækwəd/ &nbsp; adv. 向后<br />challenge &nbsp; /ˈtʃæləndʒ/ &nbsp; n. 挑战<br />being back in the maze 与 hunting for cheese 在文中属于动名词作主语<br />nearly &nbsp; /ˈnɪəli/ &nbsp; adv. &nbsp;几乎，差不多<br />as bad as.... &nbsp; 如....一样的坏（差）<br /></strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></p>', 1499586484, 141, 110, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'There''s a haze to get through before the right way.', '穿过迷雾重重，才能找到对路。'),
(45, 0, '第41节', '记得提醒自己', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170712/vedio_2771499851097.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170712/1499851096852019.jpg', '<p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;"></span></p><p><strong>As time went on he began to wonder if it was realistic for him to expect to find New Cheese. He wondered if he had bitten off more than he could chew. Then he laughed, realizing that he had nothing to chew on at that moment. </strong></p><p><strong>Whenever he started to get discouraged, he reminded himself &nbsp;that what he was doing, as uncomfortable as it was at the moment, was in reality much better than staying in the Cheeseless situation. He was taking control, rather than simply letting things happen to him. </strong></p><p><strong>Then he reminded himself, if Sniff and Scurry could move on, so could he.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;"></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;">realistic &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˌriəˈlɪstɪk/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 实际的，可行的<br />expect &nbsp; &nbsp; /ɪkˈspekt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 期望，期待<br />expect to do &nbsp;期望做某事<br />bite off &nbsp; &nbsp;咬下，咬掉<br />more than &nbsp; &nbsp;多于....<br />chew &nbsp; &nbsp;/tʃu:/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 咀嚼，咬<br />realize &nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈriəlaɪz/ &nbsp; v. 意识到（文中此处语法是非谓语动词的主动伴随）</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />discouraged &nbsp; &nbsp;/dɪs''kʌrɪdʒd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 沮丧的，灰心的<br />remind &nbsp; &nbsp;/rɪˈmaɪnd/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 提醒，使想起<br />as....as.... 结构在此句中表达让步，意为“尽管....”<br />uncomfortable &nbsp; &nbsp;/ʌnˈkʌmfətəbl/ &nbsp; &nbsp;adj. 不舒服的<br />in reality &nbsp; &nbsp;事实上<br />take control &nbsp; &nbsp;控制，掌控局面<br />rather than &nbsp; 而不是....<br />so could he &nbsp; 他也可以（这是一个完全倒装句）</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Helvetica, sans-serif;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />​<br /></span></p>', 1499851097, 142, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Don''t forget to remind yourself of the right thing. It works.', '别忘记提醒自己正确的事，会起作用的。');
INSERT INTO `lr_product` (`id`, `shop_id`, `name`, `intro`, `papers`, `thetime`, `longtime`, `user`, `price`, `photo_x`, `content`, `addtime`, `sort`, `renqi`, `type`, `del`, `del_time`, `cid`, `is_free`, `english`, `chinese`) VALUES
(47, 0, '第43节', '决心调整自己', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170720/vedio_3011500531954.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170720/1500531954574098.png', '<p><strong>Haw now realized that the change probably would not have taken him by surprise if he had been watching what was happening all along and if he had anticipated change. Maybe that''s what Sniff and Scurry had been doing. </strong></p><p><strong>He decided he would stay more alert from now on. He would expect change to happen and look for it. He would trust his basic instincts to sense when change was going to occur and be ready to adapt to it. </strong></p><p><strong>He stopped for a rest and wrote on the wall of the Maze:</strong></p><p><strong>Smell The Cheese Often </strong></p><p><strong>So You Know </strong></p><p><strong>When It Is Getting Old.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></p><p><strong>单词&amp;短语<br />take sb by surprise &nbsp; 给某人一个意外<br />all along &nbsp; 一直，一路下来<br />anticipate &nbsp; /æn''tɪsɪpeɪt/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 期望，预料<br />stay &nbsp; /steɪ/ &nbsp; v. 在文中意思是“保持”<br />alert &nbsp; /ə''lɜː(r)t/ &nbsp; adj. 警惕的，警觉的<br />from now on &nbsp; 从现在开始</strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />expect sth. to happen &nbsp; &nbsp;期待某事发生<br />trust &nbsp; &nbsp;/trʌst/ &nbsp; v. 相信，信任<br />basic &nbsp; /''beɪsɪk/ &nbsp; adj. 基本的<br />instinct &nbsp; &nbsp;/''ɪnstɪŋkt/ &nbsp; n. 直觉，本能<br />sense &nbsp; &nbsp;/sens/ &nbsp; v. 感觉<br />occur &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''kɜː(r)/ &nbsp; &nbsp;v. 发生<br />adapt &nbsp; &nbsp;/ə''dæpt/ &nbsp; v. 适应<br />adapt to sth. &nbsp;适应某事物<br /></strong></p><p><strong><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></strong></p>', 1500531954, 144, 110, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Adjust and adapt yourself.', '调整自己，适应环境。'),
(48, 0, '第44节', '心理落差要自己调整', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170803/vedio_5771501741332.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170803/1501741332120289.png', '<p style="text-align:left;">Sometime later, after not finding Cheese for what seemed like a long time, Haw finally came across a huge Cheese Station, which looked promising. When he went inside, however, he was most disappointed to discover that the Cheese Station was empty. <br />“This empty feeling has happened to me too often,” he thought. He felt like giving up. <br />Haw was losing his physical strength. He knew he was lost and was afraid he would not survive. He thought about turning around and heading back to Cheese Station C. At least, if he made it back, and Hem was still there, Haw wouldn’t be alone. Then he asked himself the same question again, “What would I do if I weren’t afraid?” </p><p style="text-align:left;"><strong><span style="color:black;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:16px;"><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></span></span></strong></p><p style="text-align:left;"><strong><span style="color:black;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:16px;"></span></span></strong></p><div>单词&amp;短语<br />what seemed like a long time&nbsp;&nbsp; 看上去似乎挺长的一段时间<br />come across&nbsp;&nbsp; 偶遇，遇到<br />promising&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈprɒmɪsɪŋ/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 前途光明的，有希望的<br />disappointed&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˌdɪsəˈpɔɪntɪd/&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 失望的<br />discover&nbsp;&nbsp; /dɪˈskʌvə(r)/&nbsp;&nbsp; v. 发现<br />empty&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈempti/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 空的，空无一物</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />feel like doing&nbsp;&nbsp; 想要做某事<br />give up 放弃<br />physical&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈfɪzɪkl/&nbsp; adj. 身体上的，物质上的<br />strength&nbsp;&nbsp; /strɛŋkθ/&nbsp;&nbsp; n. 力量<br />survive&nbsp;&nbsp; /səˈvaɪv/&nbsp;&nbsp; v. 幸存，幸免于难<br />at least&nbsp; 至少（翻译短语 at most 至多）<br />alone&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /əˈləʊn/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 独自的，孤单的</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></div><p></p>', 1501741332, 145, 145, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Once you set out, there''s no going back.', '一旦出发，便没有回头路。'),
(49, 0, 'P25-27', '故事的前3页', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170804/vedio_3011501813185.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170804/1501813185848920.jpg', '<p>Once, long ago in a land far away, there lived four little characters who ran through the maze looking for cheese to nourish them and make them happy. <br />Two were mice, named “Sniff” and “Scurry”, and two were Littlepeople—beings who were as small as mice but who looked and acted a lot like people today. Their names were “Hem” and “Haw”. <br />Due to their small size, it would be easy not to notice what the four of them were doing. But if you looked closely enough, you could discover the most amazing things. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Every day the mice and the Littlepeople spent time in the maze looking for their own special cheese. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, possessing simple brains and good instincts, searched for the hard nibbling cheese they liked, as mice often do.<br />The two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, used their complex brains, filled with many beliefs and emotions, to search for a very different kind of cheese—with a capital C—which they believed would make them feel happy and successful. <br />As different as the mice and the Littlepeople were, they shared something in common: every morning, they each put on their jogging suits and running shoes, left their little homes, and raced out into the maze looking for their favorite cheese. <br />The maze was a labyrinth of corridors and chambers, some containing delicious cheese. But there were also dark corners and blind alleys leading nowhere. It was an easy place for anyone to get lost. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />However, for those who found their way, the Maze held secrets that let them enjoy a better life. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, used the simple trial-and-error method of finding cheese. They ran down one corridor, and if it proved empty, they turned and ran down another. They remembered the corridors that held no cheese and quickly went into new areas.<br />Sniff would smell out the general direction of the cheese, using his great nose, and Scurry would race ahead. They got lost, as you might expect, went off in the wrong direction and often bumped into walls. But after a while, they found their way. <br />Like the mice, the two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, also used their ability to think and learn their past experiences. However, they relied on their complex brains to develop more sophisticated methods of finding cheese. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Sometimes they did well, but at other times their powerful human beliefs and emotions took over and clouded the way they looked at things. It made life in the maze more complicated and challenging. <br />Nonetheless, Sniff, Scurry, Hem and Haw all discovered, in their own way, what they were looking for. They each found their own kind of cheese one day at the end of one of the corridors in Cheese Station C. <br /></p>', 1501813185, 111, 111, 0, 1, 1501990360, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(50, 0, 'Audio 1', '故事的 P25-27', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170804/vedio_9571501814238.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170804/1501814238508769.jpg', '<p>Once, long ago in a land far away, there lived four little characters who ran through a maze looking for cheese to nourish them and make them happy. <br />Two were mice, named “Sniff” and “Scurry”, and two were Littlepeople—beings who were as small as mice but who looked and acted a lot like people today. Their names were “Hem” and “Haw”. <br />Due to their small size, it would be easy not to notice what the four of them were doing. But if you looked closely enough, you could discover the most amazing things. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Every day the mice and the Littlepeople spent time in the maze looking for their own special cheese. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, possessing simple brains and good instincts, searched for the hard nibbling cheese they liked, as mice often do.<br />The two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, used their complex brains, filled with many beliefs and emotions, to search for a very different kind of cheese—with a capital C—which they believed would make them feel happy and successful. <br />As different as the mice and the Littlepeople were, they shared something in common: every morning, they each put on their jogging suits and running shoes, left their little homes, and raced out into the maze looking for their favorite cheese. <br />The maze was a labyrinth of corridors and chambers, some containing delicious cheese. But there were also dark corners and blind alleys leading nowhere. It was an easy place for anyone to get lost. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />However, for those who found their way, the Maze held secrets that let them enjoy a better life. <br />The mice, Sniff and Scurry, used the simple trial-and-error method of finding cheese. They ran down one corridor, and if it proved empty, they turned and ran down another. They remembered the corridors that held no cheese and quickly went into new areas.<br />Sniff would smell out the general direction of the cheese, using his great nose, and Scurry would race ahead. They got lost, as you might expect, went off in the wrong direction and often bumped into walls. But after a while, they found their way. <br />Like the mice, the two Littlepeople, Hem and Haw, also used their ability to think and learn from their past experiences. However, they relied on their complex brains to develop more sophisticated methods of finding cheese. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Sometimes they did well, but at other times their powerful human beliefs and emotions took over and clouded the way they looked at things. It made life in the maze more complicated and challenging. <br />Nonetheless, Sniff, Scurry, Hem and Haw all discovered, in their own way, what they were looking for. They each found their own kind of cheese one day at the end of one of the corridors in Cheese Station C. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1501814238, 2, 123, 1, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(55, 0, 'Audio 5', '故事的 P39-41', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170820/vedio_5091503222818.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170820/1503222818108985.jpg', '<p>While Hem and Haw were still trying to decide what to do, Sniff and Scurry were already well on their way. They went farther into the Maze, up and down corridors, looking for Cheese in every Cheese Station they could find. <br />They didn''t think of anything else but finding New Cheese. <br />They didn''t find any for some time until they finally went into an area of the maze where they had never been before: Cheese Station N. <br />They squealed with delight. They found what they had been looking for: a great supply of New Cheese. <br />They could hardly believe their eyes. It was the biggest store of cheese the mice had ever seen. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />In the meantime, Hem and Haw were still back in Cheese Station C evaluating their situation. They were now suffering from the effects of having no Cheese. They were becoming frustrated and angry and were blaming each other for the situation they were in. <br />Now and then Haw thought about his mice friends, Sniff and Scurry, and wondered if they had found any Cheese yet. He believed they might be having a hard time, as running through the maze usually involved some uncertainty. But he also knew that it was likely to only last for a while. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Sometimes Haw would imagine Sniff and Scurry finding New Cheese and enjoying it.&nbsp;He thought about how good it would be for him to be out on an adventure in the maze, and to find fresh New Cheese. He could almost taste it. <br />The more clearly Haw saw the image of himself finding and enjoying the New Cheese, the more he saw himself leaving Cheese Station C. <br />&quot;Let''s go!&quot; He exclaimed, all of a sudden. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />&quot;No,&quot; Hem quickly responded. &quot;I like it here. It''s comfortable. It''s what I know. Besides it''s dangerous out there.&quot; <br />&quot;No, it isn''t,&quot; Haw argued. &quot;We''ve run through many parts of the maze before, and we can do it again.&quot; <br />&quot;I''m getting too old for that,&quot; Hem said. &quot;And I''m afraid I''m not interested in getting lost and making a fool of myself. Are you?&quot; <br />With that, Haw''s fear of failing returned and his hope of finding New Cheese faded. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />So every day, the Little people continued to do what they had done before. They went to Cheese Station C, found no Cheese, and returned home, carrying their worries and frustrations with them. <br />They tried to deny what was happening, but found it harder to get to sleep, had less energy the next day, and were becoming irritable. <br />Their homes were not the nurturing places they once were. The Little people had difficulty sleeping and were having nightmares about not finding any Cheese. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1503222818, 6, 111, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(56, 0, '第46节', '遇见灵魂', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170822/vedio_8901503393738.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170822/1503394565686161.jpg', '<div>Haw looked down the dark passageway and was aware of his fear. What lay ahead? Was it empty? Or worse, were there dangers lurking? He began to imagine all kinds of frightening things that could happen to him. He was scaring himself to death. <br />Then he laughed at himself. He realized his fears were making things worse. So he did what he would do if he weren’t afraid. He moved in a new direction. <br />As he started running down the dark corridor he began to smile. Haw didn’t realize it yet, but he was discovering what nourished his soul. He was letting go and trusting what lay ahead for him, even though he did not know exactly what it was. <br />To his surprise, Haw started to enjoy himself more and more. “Why do I feel so good?” he wondered. “I don’t have any Cheese and I don’t know where I am going.”<br />Before long, he knew why he felt good. <br />He stopped to write again on the wall:<br />When You Stop Being Afraid, You Feel Good. </div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div><div>单词&amp;短语<br />aware&nbsp;&nbsp; /əˈweə(r)/&nbsp; adj. 意识到的，了解的（搭配短语 be aware of sth.） <br />lay&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/leɪ/&nbsp; v. lie的过去式，字面为躺着，在此理解为存在着<br />lurk&nbsp;&nbsp; /lɜ:k/&nbsp; v. 潜伏，潜藏（文中语法点是非谓语动词的主动伴随）<br />frightening&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈfraɪtnɪŋ/&nbsp; adj. 吓人的，令人感到害怕的<br />scare &nbsp; /skeə(r)/&nbsp; v. 吓人，惊吓<br />nourish&nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈnʌrɪʃ/&nbsp; v. 滋养，抚养，使健壮<br />let go&nbsp; &nbsp;放手，放开，放下<br />to one’s surprise, ……&nbsp;&nbsp; 令某人感到惊讶的是……<br />before long&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 不久之后（参考语法精华课程1月9日内容）</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />海海老师编注：音频中所说，黑暗是引发内心恐惧的最大诱因，是因为黑暗意味着未知，所以未知才是恐惧的最大诱因，特此补充。</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div>', 1503393738, 147, 147, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'Nothing feels better than when you meet your soul.', '当你遇见灵魂，世间无物可比。'),
(51, 0, 'Audio 2', '故事的 P28-31', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170807/vedio_9861502074376.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170807/1502074376560274.jpg', '<p>Every morning after that, the mice and the Littlepeople dressed in their running gear and headed over to Cheese Station C. It wasn’t long before they each established their own routine. <br />Sniff and Scurry continued to wake early every day and race through the Maze, always following the same route. <br />When they arrived at their destination, the mice took off their running shoes, tied them together and hung them around their necks—so they could get to them quickly whenever they needed them again. Then they enjoyed the cheese. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />In the beginning Hem and Haw also raced toward Cheese Station C every morning to enjoy the tasty new morsels that awaited them. But after a while, a different routine set in for the Littlepeople. <br />Hem and Haw awoke each day a little later, dressed a little slower, and walked to Cheese Station C. After all, they knew where the cheese was now and where to find them. <br />They had no idea where the cheese came from, or who put it there. They just assumed it would be there. <br />As soon as as Hem and Haw arrived at Cheese Station C each morning, they settled in and made themselves at home. They hung up their jogging suits, put away their running shoes and put on their slippers. They were becoming very comfortable now that they had found the cheese. <br />“This is great,” Hem said, “There’s enough cheese here to last us forever.” The Littlepeople felt happy and successful, and thought they were now secure. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />It wasn’t long before Hem and Haw regarded the cheese they found at Cheese Station C as their cheese. It was such a large store of cheese that they eventually moved their homes to be closer to it, and built a social life around it. <br />To make themselves feel more at home, Hem and Haw decorated the walls with sayings and even drew pictures of cheese around them which made them smile. One read:<br />Having Cheese Makes You Happy. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Sometimes Hem and Haw would take their friends by to see their pile of cheese at Cheese Station C, and point to it with pride, saying, “Pretty nice cheese, huh?” Sometimes they shared it with their friends and sometimes they didn’t. <br />“We deserve this cheese,” Hem said. “We certainly had to work long and hard enough to find it.” He picked up a nice fresh piece and ate it. <br />Afterward, Hem fell asleep, as he often did. <br />Every night the Littlepeople would waddle home, full of cheese, and every morning they would confidently return for more. <br />This went on for quite some time. <br />After a while Hem’s and Haw’s confidence grew into the arrogance of success. Soon they became so comfortable they didn’t even notice what was happening. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1502074376, 3, 123, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(52, 0, 'Audio 3', '故事的 P32-34', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170810/vedio_1721502332017.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170810/1502332017327939.jpg', '<p>As time went on, Sniff and Scurry continued their routine. They arrived early each morning and sniffed and scratched and scurried around Cheese Station C, inspecting the area to see if there had been any changes from the day before. Then they would sit down to nibble on the cheese. <br />One morning, they arrived at Cheese Station C and discovered there was no cheese. <br />They weren’t surprised. Since Sniff and Scurry had noticed the supply of cheese had been getting smaller every day, they were prepared for the inevitable and knew instinctively what to do. <br />They looked at each other, removed the running shoes they had tied together and hung conveniently around their necks, put them on their feet and laced them up. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />The mice did not overanalyze things. <br />To the mice, the problem and the answer were both simple. The situation at Cheese Station C had changed. So, Sniff and Scurry decided to change. <br />They both looked out into the maze. Then Sniff lifted his nose, sniffed, and nodded to Scurry, who took off running through the maze, while Sniff followed as fast as he could. <br />They were quickly off in search of new cheese. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Later that same day, Hem and Haw arrived at Cheese Station C. They had not been paying attention to the small changes that had been taking place each day, so they took it for granted their cheese would be there. <br />They were unprepared for what they found. <br />“What! No Cheese?” Hem yelled. He continued yelling, “No cheese? No cheese?” as though if he shouted loud enough someone would put it back. <br />“Who moved my cheese?” he hollered. <br />Finally, he put his hands on his hips, his face turned red, and he screamed at the top of his voice, “It’s not fair!” </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Haw just shook his head in disbelief. He, too, had counted on finding cheese at Cheese Station C. He stood there for a long time, frozen with shock. He was just not ready for this. <br />Hem was yelling something, but Haw didn’t want to hear it. He didn’t want to deal with what was facing him, so he just tuned everything out. <br />The Littlepeople’s behavior was not very attractive or productive, but it was understandable. <br />Finding cheese wasn''t easy, and it meant a great deal more to the Littlepeople than just having enough of it to eat every day. Finding cheese was the Littlepeople''s way of getting what they thought they needed to be happy. They had their own ideas of what Cheese meant to them, depending on their taste.&nbsp; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />For some, having Cheese was having material things. For others it was enjoying good health or developing a spiritual sense of well-being. <br />For Haw, Cheese just meant feeling safe, having a loving family someday and living in a cozy cottage on Cheddar Lane. <br />To Hem, Cheese was becoming a Big Cheese in charge of others and owning a big house atop Camembert Hill. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1502332017, 4, 201, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(53, 0, 'Audio 4', '故事的 P35-38', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170813/vedio_2591502596591.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170813/1502596777494981.jpg', '<p>Because Cheese was important to them, the two Little people spent a long time trying to decide what to do. All they could think of was to keep looking around Cheeseless Station C to see if the Cheese was really gone. <br />While Sniff and Scurry had quickly moved on, Hem and Haw continued to hem and haw. <br />They ranted and raved at the injustice of it all. Haw started to get depressed. What would happen if the Cheese wasn''t there tomorrow? He had made future plans based on this Cheese. <br />The Little people couldn''t believe it. How could this have happened? No one had warned them. It wasn''t right. It was not the way things were supposed to be. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Hem and Haw went home that night hungry and discouraged. But before they left, Haw wrote on the wall: <br />The More Important Your Cheese Is To You, The More You Want To Hold On To It. <br />The next day Hem and Haw left their homes, and returned to Cheese Station C again, where they still expected, somehow, to find their Cheese. <br />The situation hadn''t changed, the Cheese was no longer there. The Little people didn''t know what to do. Hem and Haw just stood there, immobilized like two statues. <br />Haw shut his eyes as tight as he could and put his hands over his ears. He just wanted to block everything out. He didn''t want to know the Cheese supply had gradually been getting smaller. He believed it had been moved all of a sudden. <br />Hem analyzed the situation over and over and eventually his complicated brain with its huge belief system took hold. &quot;Why did they do this to me?&quot; he demanded. &quot;What''s really going on here?&quot; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Finally, Haw opened his eyes, looked around and said, &quot;By the way, where are Sniff and Scurry? Do you think they know something we don''t?&quot; <br />Hem scoffed, &quot;What would they know?&quot; <br />Hem continued, &quot;They''re just mice. They just respond to what happens. We''re Little people. We''re smarter than mice. We should be able to figure this out.&quot; <br />&quot;I know we''re smarter,&quot; Haw said, &quot;but we don''t seem to be acting smarter at the moment. Things are changing around here, Hem. Maybe we need to change and do things differently. &quot; <br />&quot;Why should we change?&quot; Hem asked. &quot;We''re Little people. We''re special. This sort of thing should not happen to us. Or if it does, we should at least get some benefits.&quot; <img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />&quot;Why should we get benefits?&quot; Haw asked. <br />&quot;Because we''re entitled.&quot; Hem claimed. <br />&quot;Entitled to what?&quot; Haw wanted to know. <br />&quot;We''re entitled to our Cheese.&quot; <br />&quot;Why?&quot; Haw asked. <br />&quot;Because, we didn''t cause this problem,&quot; Hem said. &quot;Somebody else did this and we should get something out of it.&quot; <br />Haw suggested, &quot;Maybe we should simply stop analyzing the situation so much and go find some New Cheese?&quot; <br />&quot;Oh no,&quot; Hem argued. &quot;I''m going to get to the bottom of this.&quot; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1502596591, 5, 100, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(54, 0, '第45节', '及时调整新方向', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170813/vedio_8971502604709.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170813/1502604709429677.png', '<div>Haw thought he was past his fear, but he was afraid more often than he liked to admit, even to himself. He wasn’t always sure what he was afraid of, but, in his weakened condition, he knew now he was simply fearful of going on alone. Haw didn’t know it, but he was running behind because he was still weighed down by fearful beliefs. <br />Haw wondered if Hem had moved on, or if he was still paralyzed by his own fears. Then, Haw remembered the times when he had felt his best in the Maze. It was when he was moving along. <br />Haw wrote on the wall, knowing it was as much a reminder to himself as it was a marking for his friend Hem, hopefully, to follow:<br />Movement In A New Direction Helps You Find New Cheese. </div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div><div>单词&amp;短语<br />past&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/pɑ:st/&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; prep. 经过，越过<br />weaken&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈwi:kən/&nbsp;&nbsp; v. 使变弱（文中用形容词形式，表示，被变弱的，虚弱的）<br />condition&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;/kənˈdɪʃn/&nbsp;&nbsp; n. 情况，状态<br />fearful&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/ˈfɪəfl/&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 害怕的（文中的短语 be fearful of，表示对…感到害怕）<br />alone&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;/əˈləʊn/&nbsp;&nbsp; adv. 单独地，独自地<br />run behind&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;落后<br />weigh down&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 把…压得喘不过气，压过<br />paralyze&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; /''pærəlaɪz/&nbsp;&nbsp; v. 使瘫痪，使麻痹</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div><div>高级句型<br />It is as much A as it is B. 它既是A，也是B。（同时担任2个角色，或起2种作用）</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></div>', 1502604709, 146, 146, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'It is as much the end of a story as it is the beginning of another.', '这是一个故事的结尾，也是另一个故事的开头。'),
(57, 0, 'VIP会员', '笔记发布入口', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170824/vedio_1341503565211.mp3', '4:26', 266, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170824/1503564933386770.jpg', '此处为VIP会员完成返现活动任务的笔记发布入口，请点击右上角“写笔记”，发布笔记图片。', 1503564697, 2, 0, 0, 1, 1503565320, 1, 1, '', ''),
(58, 0, 'Audio 6', '故事的 P42-46', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170901/vedio_4991504238457.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170901/1504238982789984.jpg', '<p>But Hem and Haw still returned to Cheese Station C and waited there every day. <br />Hem said, &quot;You know if we just work harder we''ll find that nothing has really changed that much. The Cheese is probably nearby. Maybe they just hid it behind the wall.&quot; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />The next day, Hem and Haw returned with tools. Hem held the chisel, while Haw banged on the hammer until they made a hole in the wall of Cheese Station C. They peered inside but found no Cheese. <br />They were disappointed but believed they could solve the problem. So they started earlier, stayed longer, and worked harder. But after a while, all they had was a large hole in the wall. <br />Haw was beginning to realize the difference between activity and productivity. <br />&quot;Maybe,&quot; Hem said, &quot;we should just sit here and see what happens. Sooner or later they have to put the Cheese back.&quot; <br />Haw wanted to believe that. So each day he went home to rest and returned reluctantly with Hem to Cheese Station C. But Cheese never reappeared. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />By now the Little people were growing weak from hunger and stress. Haw was getting tired of just waiting for their situation to improve. He began to see that the longer they stayed in their Cheeseless situation, the worse off they would be. <br />Haw knew they were losing their edge. <br />Finally, one day Haw began laughing at himself. &quot;Haw, haw, look at us. We keep doing the same things over and over again and wonder why things don''t get better. If this wasn''t so ridiculous, it would be even funnier.&quot;&nbsp; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Haw did not like the idea of having to run through the maze again, because he knew he would get lost and have no idea where he would find any Cheese. But he had to laugh at his folly when he saw what his fear was doing to him. <br />He asked Hem, &quot;Where did we put our running shoes?&quot; It took a long time to find them because they had put everything away when they found their Cheese at Cheese Station C, thinking they wouldn''t be needing them anymore. <br />As Hem saw his friend getting into his running gear, he said, &quot;You''re not really going out into the maze again, are you? Why don''t you just wait here with me until they put the Cheese back?&quot; </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />&quot;Because, you just don''t get it.&quot; Haw said. &quot;I didn''t want to see it either, but now I realize they''re never going to put yesterday''s Cheese back. It''s time to find New Cheese.&quot; <br />Hem argued, &quot;But what if there''s no Cheese out there? Or even if there is, what if you don''t find it?&quot; <br />&quot;I don''t know,&quot; Haw said. He had asked himself those same questions too many times and felt the fears again that kept him where he was. <br />He asked himself, &quot;Where am I more likely to find Cheese—here or in the maze?&quot; <br />He painted a picture in his mind. He saw himself venturing out into the maze with a smile on his face. <br />While this picture surprised him, it made him feel good. He saw himself getting lost now and then in the maze, but felt confident he would eventually find New Cheese out there and all the good things that came with it. He gathered his courage. <br />Then he used his imagination to paint the most believable picture he could — with the most realistic details — of him finding and enjoying the taste of New Cheese. <br />He saw himself eating Swiss cheese with holes in it, bright orange Cheddar and American cheeses, Italian Mozzarella and wonderfully soft French Camembert Cheese, and...... <br />Then he heard Hem say something and realized they were still at Cheese Station C. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br />Haw said,&quot; Sometimes, Hem, things change and they are never the same again. This looks like one of those times. That''s life! Life moves on. And so should we.&quot; <br />Haw looked at his emaciated companion and tried to talk sense to him, but Hem''s fear had turned into anger and he wouldn''t listen. <br />Haw didn''t mean to be rude to his friend, but he had to laugh at how silly they both looked. <br />As Haw prepared to leave, he started to feel more alive, knowing that he was finally able to laugh at himself, let go and move on. <br />Haw laughed and announced, &quot;It''s...Maze...time!&quot; <br />Hem didn''t laugh and he didn''t respond. <br />Haw picked up and small, sharp rock and wrote a serious thought on the wall for Hem to think about. As was his custom, Haw even drew a picture of Cheese around it, hoping it would help Hem to smile, lighten up, and go after the New Cheese. But Hem didn''t want to see it. <br />It read: <br />If You Do Not Change, You Can Become Extinct. </p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1504238458, 7, 7, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(59, 0, '第47节 带读版', 'P57-58', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170902/vedio_9021504334027.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170902/1504334191465909.jpg', 'Haw realized he had been held captive by his own fear. Moving in a new direction had freed him.&nbsp;<br />Now he felt the cool breeze that was blowing in this part of the Maze and it was refreshing. He took in some deep breaths and felt invigorated by the movement. Once he had gotten past his fear, it turned out to be more enjoyable than he once believed it could be.&nbsp;<br />Haw hadn’t felt this way for a long time. He had almost forgotten how much fun it was to go for it.&nbsp;<br />To make things even better, Haw started to paint a picture in his mind again. He saw himself in great realistic detail, sitting in the middle of a pile of all his favorite cheeses—from Cheddar to Brie! He saw himself eating the many cheeses he liked, and he enjoyed what he saw. Then he imagined how much he would enjoy all their great tastes.&nbsp;<br />The more clearly he saw the image of himself enjoying New Cheese, the more real and believable it became. He could sense that he was going to find it.&nbsp;<br />He wrote:<br /><p>Imagining Yourself Enjoying Your New Cheese Leads You To It.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1504334027, 8, 8, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(60, 0, '第47节', '追寻自由', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170902/vedio_6911504341925.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170902/1504342250631175.jpg', '<div>Haw realized he had been held captive by his own fear. Moving in a new direction had freed him. <br />Now he felt the cool breeze that was blowing in this part of the Maze and it was refreshing. He took in some deep breaths and felt invigorated by the movement. Once he had gotten past his fear, it turned out to be more enjoyable than he once believed it could be. <br />Haw hadn’t felt this way for a long time. He had almost forgotten how much fun it was to go for it. <br />To make things even better, Haw started to paint a picture in his mind again. He saw himself in great realistic detail, sitting in the middle of a pile of all his favorite cheeses—from Cheddar to Brie! He saw himself eating the many cheeses he liked, and he enjoyed what he saw. Then he imagined how much he would enjoy all their great tastes. <br />The more clearly he saw the image of himself enjoying New Cheese, the more real and believable it became. He could sense that he was going to find it. <br />He wrote:<br />Imagining Yourself Enjoying Your New Cheese Leads You To It. </div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div><div>单词&amp;短语<br />captive &nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈkæptɪv/&nbsp; adj. 被俘虏的<br />hold sb. captive&nbsp; 把某人俘虏<br />breeze &nbsp;&nbsp; /bri:z/&nbsp; n. 微风<br />refreshing &nbsp; &nbsp; /rɪˈfreʃɪŋ/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 清新的，提神的<br />invigorated &nbsp;&nbsp; /ɪnˈvɪgəreɪtid/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 精神振奋的，精力充沛的<br />realistic &nbsp;&nbsp; /ˌri:əˈlɪstɪk/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 真实的，逼真的<br />believable &nbsp;&nbsp; /bɪˈli:vəbl/&nbsp;&nbsp; adj. 可信的<br />sense &nbsp;&nbsp; /sens/&nbsp;&nbsp; v. 感觉，感到</div><div>关于动名词做主语的语法点，请参考【语法精华课】6月16日内容</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /></div><div>句子精选<br />He had almost forgotten how much fun it was to go for it. <br />他几乎忘记了去追寻自由是多么地有意思。</div><div><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></div>', 1504341925, 148, 148, 0, 0, 0, 1, 2, 'It is so much fun to move without fear and go for freedom.', '抛开恐惧追寻自由，是多么地有意思。'),
(61, 0, 'Audio 7', '故事的 P47-52', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170903/vedio_4931504424769.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170903/1504424769464991.jpg', 'Then, Haw stuck his head out and peered anxiously into the maze. He thought about how he''d gotten himself into this cheeseless situation.&nbsp;<br />He had believed that there may not be any Cheese in the maze, or he may not find it. Such fearful beliefs were immobilizing and killing him.&nbsp;<br /><p>Haw smiled. He knew Hem was wondering, &quot;Who moved my cheese?&quot; But Haw was wondering, &quot;Why didn''t I get up and move with the Cheese sooner?&quot;&nbsp;</p>As he started out into the maze, Haw looked back to where he had come from and felt its comfort. He could feel himself being drawn back into familiar territory — even thought he hadn''t found Cheese here for some time.&nbsp;<br />Haw became more anxious and wondered if he really wanted to go out into the maze. He wrote a saying on the wall ahead of him and stared at it for some time:&nbsp;<br /><p>What Would You Do If You Weren''t Afraid?&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>He thought about it. He knew sometimes some fear can be good. When you are afraid things are going to get worse if you don''t do something, it can prompt you into action. But it is not good when you are so afraid that it keeps you from doing anything.&nbsp;<br />He looked to his right, to the part of the maze where he had never been, and felt the fear.&nbsp;<br />Then, he took a deep breath, turned right into the maze, and jogged slowly, into the unknown.&nbsp;<br />As he tried to find his way, Haw worried, at first, that he might have waited too long in Cheese Station C. He hadn''t had any cheese for so long that he was now weak. It took him longer and it was more painful than usual to get through the maze.&nbsp;<br />He decided that if he ever got the chance again, he would get out of his comfort zone and adapt to change sooner. It would make things easier.&nbsp;<br /><p>Then, Haw smiled a weak smile as he thought, &quot;Better late than never.&quot;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>During the next several days, Haw found a little Cheese here and there, but nothing that lasted very long. He had hoped to find enough Cheese to take some back to Hem and encourage him to come out into the Maze.&nbsp;<br />But Haw didn''t feel confident enough yet. He had to admit he found it confusing in the Maze. Things seemed to have changed since the last time he was out here.&nbsp;<br /><p>Just when he thought he was getting ahead, he would get lost in the corridors. It seemed his progress was two steps forward and one step backward. It was a challenge, but he had to admit that being back in the Maze, hunting for Cheese, wasn''t nearly as bad as he feared it might be.</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>As time went on he began to wonder if it was realistic for him to expect to find New Cheese. He wondered if he had bitten off more than he could chew. Then he laughed, realizing that he had nothing to chew on at that moment.&nbsp;<br />Whenever he started to get discouraged, he reminded himself that what he was doing, as uncomfortable as it was at the moment, was in reality much better than staying in the Cheeseless situation. He was taking control, rather than simply letting things happen to him.&nbsp;<br /><p>Then he reminded himself, if Sniff and Scurry could move on, so could he.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>Later, as Haw looked back on things, he realized that the Cheese at Cheese Station C had not just disappeared overnight, as he had once believed. The amount of Cheese that had been there toward the end had been getting smaller, and what was left had grown old. It didn’t taste as good.&nbsp;<br />Mold may even have begun to grow on the old Cheese, although he hadn’t noticed it. He had to admit, however, that if he had wanted to, he probably could have seen what was coming. But he didn’t.&nbsp;<br />Haw now realized that the change probably would not have taken him by surprise if he had been watching what was happening all along and if he had anticipated change. Maybe that''s what Sniff and Scurry had been doing.&nbsp;<br />He decided he would stay more alert from now on. He would expect change to happen and look for it. He would trust his basic instincts to sense when change was going to occur and be ready to adapt to it.&nbsp;<br />He stopped for a rest and wrote on the wall of the Maze:<br />Smell The Cheese Often&nbsp;So You Know When It Is Getting Old.&nbsp;<p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1504424769, 9, 9, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。'),
(62, 0, 'Audio 8', '故事的 P53-58', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20170904/vedio_6341504493217.mp3', NULL, 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20170904/1504493217566838.jpg', 'Sometime later, after not finding Cheese for what seemed like a long time, Haw finally came across a huge Cheese Station, which looked promising. When he went inside, however, he was most disappointed to discover that the Cheese Station was empty.&nbsp;<br />“This empty feeling has happened to me too often,” he thought. He felt like giving up.&nbsp;<br /><p>Haw was losing his physical strength. He knew he was lost and was afraid he would not survive. He thought about turning around and heading back to Cheese Station C. At least, if he made it back, and Hem was still there, Haw wouldn’t be alone. Then he asked himself the same question again, “What would I do if I weren’t afraid?”&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>Haw thought he was past his fear, but he was afraid more often than he liked to admit, even to himself. He wasn’t always sure what he was afraid of, but, in his weakened condition, he knew now he was simply fearful of going on alone. Haw didn’t know it, but he was running behind because he was still weighed down by fearful beliefs.&nbsp;<br />Haw wondered if Hem had moved on, or if he was still paralyzed by his own fears. Then, Haw remembered the times when he had felt his best in the Maze. It was when he was moving along.&nbsp;<br />Haw wrote on the wall, knowing it was as much a reminder to himself as it was a marking for his friend Hem, hopefully, to follow:<br /><p>Movement In A New Direction Helps You Find New Cheese.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>Haw looked down the dark passageway and was aware of his fear. What lay ahead? Was it empty? Or worse, were there dangers lurking? He began to imagine all kinds of frightening things that could happen to him. He was scaring himself to death.&nbsp;<br />Then he laughed at himself. He realized his fears were making things worse. So he did what he would do if he weren’t afraid. He moved in a new direction.&nbsp;<br />As he started running down the dark corridor he began to smile. Haw didn’t realize it yet, but he was discovering what nourished his soul. He was letting go and trusting what lay ahead for him, even though he did not know exactly what it was.&nbsp;<br />To his surprise, Haw started to enjoy himself more and more. “Why do I feel so good?” he wondered. “I don’t have any Cheese and I don’t know where I am going.”<br />Before long, he knew why he felt good.&nbsp;<br />He stopped to write again on the wall:<br /><p>When You Stop Being Afraid, You Feel Good.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>Haw realized he had been held captive by his own fear. Moving in a new direction had freed him.&nbsp;<br />Now he felt the cool breeze that was blowing in this part of the Maze and it was refreshing. He took in some deep breaths and felt invigorated by the movement. Once he had gotten past his fear, it turned out to be more enjoyable than he once believed it could be.&nbsp;<br />Haw hadn’t felt this way for a long time. He had almost forgotten how much fun it was to go for it.&nbsp;<br />To make things even better, Haw started to paint a picture in his mind again. He saw himself in great realistic detail, sitting in the middle of a pile of all his favorite cheeses—from Cheddar to Brie! He saw himself eating the many cheeses he liked, and he enjoyed what he saw. Then he imagined how much he would enjoy all their great tastes.&nbsp;<br />The more clearly he saw the image of himself enjoying New Cheese, the more real and believable it became. He could sense that he was going to find it.&nbsp;<br />He wrote:<br /><p>Imagining Yourself Enjoying Your New Cheese Leads You To It.&nbsp;</p><p><img alt="生气" src="/miniread/Public/plugins/xheditor/xheditor_emot/default/mad.gif" /><br /></p>', 1504493217, 10, 10, 0, 0, 0, 2, 1, 'In reading you find yourself.', '阅读，找到自己。');
