(425, 0, 'wanna gonna 到底是什么？', '俚语其实是发音', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171118/vedio_7531510996091.mp3', '4:51', 291, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171118/1510996519956213.jpg', '<p>1) wanna = want to &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>I wanna to go home. (X) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I wanna go home. &nbsp; &nbsp;I don''t wanna do that.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p>2) gonna = going to &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>I''m gonna take it. &nbsp; &nbsp;I''m gonna be fine. &nbsp; &nbsp; I''m gonna be freaking out. &nbsp; Everything''s gonna be fine.&nbsp;</p>', 1510996091, 74, 74, 0, 0, 0, 3, 2, '', ''),
(426, 0, 'Day 1', '内容选自《朝圣者》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171201/vedio_5381512057891.mp3', '6:16', 376, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171201/1512057891159247.jpeg', '<p style="margin: 0px; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; font-family: " helvetica="" neue="">本文选自 The Pilgrimage</p><p style="margin: 0px; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; font-family: " helvetica="" neue=""><br /></p><p style="margin: 0px; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; font-family: " helvetica="" neue="">&quot;The good fight is the one that''s fought in the name of our dreams. When we''re young and our dreams first explode inside us with all of their force, we are very courageous, but we haven''t yet learned how to fight. With great effort, we learn how to fight, but by then we no longer have the courage to go into combat. So we turn against ourselves and do battle within. We become our own worst enemy. We say that our dreams were childish, or too difficult to realize, or the result of our not having known enough about life. We kill our dreams because we are afraid to fight the good fight. &quot;</p><p style="margin: 0px; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; font-family: " helvetica="" neue=""><br /></p><p style="margin: 0px; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; font-family: " helvetica="" neue=""><br /></p>', 1512057891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(427, 0, 'Day 2', '内容选自《炼金术士》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171202/vedio_8101512150049.mp3', '4:20', 260, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171202/1512150049495353.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Alchemist 《炼金术士》（又译《牧羊少年的奇幻之旅》）</p><p>He said that when Narcissus died, the goddesses of the forest appeared and found the lake, which had been fresh water, transformed into a lake of salty tears.&nbsp;</p><p>&quot;Why do you weep?&quot; The goddesses asked.&nbsp;</p><p>&quot;I weep for Narcissus.&quot; The lake replied.&nbsp;</p><p>&quot;Ah, it is no surprise that you weep for Narcissus, &quot; they said, &quot;for though we always pursued him in the forest, you alone could comtemplate his beauty close at hand.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p>&quot;But...was Narcissus beautiful?&quot; The lake asked.&nbsp;</p><p>&quot;Who better than you to know that?&quot; The goddesses said in wonder. &quot;After all, it was by your banks that he knelt each day to contemplate himself.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p>The lake was silent for some time. Finally it said: &quot;I weep for Narcissus, but I never noticed that Narcissus was beautiful. I weep because each time he knelt beside my banks, I could see, in the depths of his eyes, my own beauty reflected.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512150049, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(428, 0, 'Day 3', '内容选自《炼金术士》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171203/vedio_5321512232368.mp3', '3:33', 213, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171203/1512232368987452.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Alchemist 《炼金术士》（又译《牧羊少年的奇幻之旅》）</p><p>&quot;You came so that you could learn about your dreams, &quot; said the old woman. &quot;And dreams are the language of God. When he speaks in our language, I can interpret what he has said. But if he speaks in the language of the soul, it is only you who can understand. But, whichever it is, I''m going to charge you for the consultation.&quot;&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1512232368, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(429, 0, 'Day 4', '内容选自《炼金术士》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171204/vedio_6431512319674.mp3', '5:39', 339, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171204/1512319674765807.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Alchemist 《炼金术士》（又译《牧羊少年奇幻之旅》）</p><p>There was a moment of silence so profound that it seemed the city was asleep. No sound from the bazaars, no arguments among the merchants, no men climbing to the towers to chant. No hope, no adventure, no old kings or personal legends, no treasure, and no pyramids. It was as if the world had fallen silent because the boy''s soul had. He sat there, staring blankly through the door of the cafe, wishing that he had died, and that everything would end forever at that moment.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512319674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(430, 0, 'Day 5', '内容选自《炼金术士》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171205/vedio_2001512444235.mp3', '3:11', 191, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171205/1512406275165134.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Alchemist 《炼金术士》（又译《牧羊少年的奇幻之旅》）</p><p>But the sheep had taught him something even more important: that there was a language in the world that everyone understood, a language the boy had used throughout the time that he was trying to improve things at the shop. It was the language of enthusiasm, of things accomplished with love and purpose, and as part of a search for something believed in and desired. Tangier was no longer a strange city, and he felt that, just as he had conquered this place, he could conquer the world.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512406275, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1512444633, 19, 2, '', ''),
(431, 0, 'Day 5', '内容选自《炼金术士》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171205/1512444694892286.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Alchemist 《炼金术士》（又译《牧羊少年的奇幻之旅》）</p><p>But the sheep had taught him something even more important: that there was a language in the world that everyone understood, a language the boy had used throughout the time that he was trying to improve things at the shop. It was the language of enthusiasm, of things accomplished with love and purpose, and as part of a search for something believed in and desired. Tangier was no longer a strange city, and he felt that, just as he had conquered this place, he could conquer the world.&nbsp;</p><div><br /></div>', 1512444694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(432, 0, 'Day 6', '内容选自《破碎故事之心》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171206/vedio_7791512491070.mp3', '3:11', 191, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171206/1512491070179131.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Heart of A Broken Story 《破碎故事之心》，点击右上角 - 关于原版阅读，进入公众号【海海English】，菜单可阅读本故事完整版</p><p>Loving you is the important thing, Miss Lester. There are some people who think love is sex and marriage and six o''clock-kisses and children, and perhaps it is, Miss Lester. But do you know what I think? I think love is a touch and yet not a touch.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512491070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(433, 0, 'Day 7', '内容选自《查泰莱夫人的情人》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171207/1512577170731394.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 Lady Chatterly''s Lover 《查泰莱夫人的情人》</p><p>Ours is essentially a tragic age, so we refuse to take it tragically. The cataclysm has happened, we are among the ruins, we start to build up new little habitats, to have new little hopes. It is rather hard work: there is now no smooth road into the future, but we go round, or scramble over the obstacles. We''ve got to live, no matter how many skies have fallen.&nbsp;</p><p>This was more or less Constance Chatterly''s position. The war had brought the roof down over her head. And she had realized that one must live and learn.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512577170, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(434, 0, 'Day 8', '内容选自《了不起的盖茨比》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171208/1512664665452236.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 The Great Gatsby 《了不起的盖茨比》</p><p>In my younger and more vulnerable years my father gave me some advice that I''ve been turning over in my mind ever since. &quot;Whenever you feel like criticizing any one, &quot; he told me, &quot;just remember that all the people in this world haven''t had the advantages that you''ve had. &quot;</p><p>He didn''t say any more but we''ve always been unusually communicative in a reserved way, and I understood that he meant a great deal more than that.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512664665, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(435, 0, 'Day 9', '内容选自《谁动了我的奶酪》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171209/vedio_6021512749358.mp3', '4:08', 248, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171209/1512749358595116.jpg', '<p>本文选择 Who Moved My Cheese? &nbsp;《谁动了我的奶酪？》</p><p>He knew sometimes some fear can be good. When you are afraid things are going to get worse if you don''t do something, it can prompt you into action. But it is not good when you are so afraid that it keeps you from doing anything.&nbsp;</p><p>Haw realized again, as he had once before, that what you are afraid of is never as bad as what you imagine. The fear you let build up in your mind is worse than the situation that actually exists.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1512749358, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(436, 0, 'Day 10', '内容选自《傲慢与偏见》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171210/vedio_3461512837812.mp3', '4:07', 247, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171210/1512837812324072.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 Pride and Prejudice 《傲慢与偏见》</p><p>It is a truth universally acknowledged that a single man in possession of a good fortune must be in want of a wife.&nbsp;</p><p>However little known the feelings or views of such a man may be on his first entering a neighborhood, this truth is so well fixed in the minds of the surrounding families, that he is considered the rightful property of some one or other of their daughters.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1512837812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(437, 0, 'Day 11', '内容选自《Think Big》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171211/vedio_5311512924176.mp3', '3:21', 201, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171211/1512924176724204.jpeg', '<p>本文选自《Think Big》</p><p>Focus and discipline are habits, skills that everyone can learn. I was the most undisciplined kid you could ever imagine. My parents could not handle me so they sent me off to a military school at a young age, where I learned discipline. Without this training, I never would have become who I am today.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1512924176, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(438, 0, 'Day 12', '内容选自《Think Big》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171212/1513008324588487.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 《Think Big》</p><p>I can tell you many stories about friends of mine who are really, really smart and amazing—the smartest people you can imagine—and yet they never made it, because they quit it. I can also tell you stories about friends of mine who were not as smart. If you gave them aptitude tests, they would score 25 percent lower. They are now some of the richest guys in the world, because they had something different: they didn''t quit. If you love something, if you really love it, you are less inclined to quit.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513008324, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(439, 0, 'Day 13', '内容选自《Think Big》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171213/1513097800449696.jpeg', '<p>本文选自《Think Big》</p><p>They feel that the world owes them something. In real life, it does not work that way. There are no guarantees that anyone will be rich and successful. Nobody owes you anything. You need to get down to earth and realize that you have to pave your own way to success by working hard and being diligent. There is no other way.&nbsp;</p><p>Sure, luck plays some part in the scheme of things. No question. But you cannot control luck. All you can do is just to look at what you have going for you, and use it to the max. Ignore what you lack. If you dwell on the negative, it is all over for you.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513097800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(440, 0, 'Day 14', '内容选自 VIP翻译课', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171214/vedio_1601513181472.mp3', '1:39', 99, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171214/1513181472547701.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 海海English VIP翻译课</p><p>Such being the case, we should think about how to minimize the tragedy and avoid such incidents, instead of maximizing the conflict.&nbsp;</p><p>事已至此，我们应该思考如何才能把悲剧化到最小和避免此类事件再次发生，而不是让矛盾最大化。</p>', 1513181472, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(441, 0, 'Day 15', '内容选自《Think Big》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171215/1513270200647491.jpeg', '<p>本文选自《Think Big》</p><p>It is true that some people are luckier than others. I have no doubt about that. You can help create your own luck, you can make things happen through hard work and intelligence. You can become luckier. The fact is, plenty of people have been able to take a bad situation or an unlucky situation and turn it around through hard work.&nbsp;</p><p>Luck does not come around often. So when it does, be sure to take full advantage of it, even if it means working very hard. When luck is on your side it is not the time to be modest or timid, it is the time to go for the biggest success you can possibly achieve. That is the true meaning of thinking big.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513270200, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(442, 0, 'Day 16', '内容选自《August》', NULL, '00:00', 0, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171216/1513383750699904.jpeg', '<p>本文选自《August》</p><p>What can I give you, my dear, if not a few pages of writing, into which a lot of memory has flowed from the time before we knew each other. I can hardly tell you anything about the later times that you don''t already know. That''s the thing—we''ve grown together over the years. I can hardly say &quot;I&quot;—usually &quot;we&quot;. Without you I''d be a different person. But you know that too. We''re not ones for great statements. Only this much—I have been lucky. C</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>', 1513383750, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(443, 0, 'Day 17', '内容选自《The view from the cheap seats》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171217/vedio_7351513471842.mp3', '4:19', 259, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171217/1513471842603927.jpg', '<p>本文选自 The view from the cheap seats</p><p>I believe that it is difficult to kill an idea because ideas are invisible and contagious, and they move fast.&nbsp;</p><p>I believe that you can set your own ideas against ideas that you dislike. That you should be free to argue, explain, clarify, debate, offend, insult, rage, mock, sing, dramatize and deny.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513471842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(444, 0, '心语嘉 12月17日', 'o 的短音句子练习', NULL, '00:00', 0, '', 0.00, NULL, '<p>Clip on clock, rat in socks.&nbsp;</p><p>Rat on clip on clock in socks.&nbsp;</p>', 1513522969, 0, 15, 0, 1, 1513818186, 8, 1, '', ''),
(445, 0, 'Day 18', '内容选自《The view from the cheap seats》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171218/vedio_4361513526799.mp3', '4:11', 251, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171218/1513526799373020.jpg', '<p>本文选自 The view from the cheap seats&nbsp;</p><p>I do not believe that burning, murdering, exploding people, smashing their heads with rocks (to let the bad ideas out), drowning them or even defeating them will work to contain ideas you do not like. Ideas spring up when you do not expect them, like weeds, and are as difficult to control.&nbsp;</p><p>I believe repressing ideas spreads ideas.&nbsp;</p>', 1513526799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(446, 0, 'Day 19', '内容选自《Satantango》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171219/vedio_8121513645011.mp3', '3:29', 209, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171219/1513645011353498.jpg', '<p>本文选自 Satantango （中文译《撒旦探戈》）</p><p>It wasn''t easy. Back then it had taken her two days to work out where she should plant her foot, what to grab for support and how to squeeze herself through what looked to be the impossibly narrow hole left by a few slats that opened under the eaves at the back of the house.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513645011, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(447, 0, 'Day 20', '内容选自《The Sense of an Ending》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171220/vedio_2221513699650.mp3', '2:40', 160, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171220/1513699650851874.jpg', '<p>本文选自 The Sense of an Ending&nbsp;</p><p>We live in time—it holds us and moulds us—but I''ve never felt I understood it very well. And I''m not referring to theories about how it bends and doubles back, or may exist elsewhere in parallel versions.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513699650, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(448, 0, 'Day 21', '内容选自《Cold Mountain》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171221/vedio_1201513818061.mp3', '2:04', 124, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171221/1513818061764646.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 Cold Mountain（中文译《冷山》）</p><p>Had it not been too dim, Inman would have read to pass the time until breakfast, for the book he was reading had the effect of settling his mind.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513818061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(449, 0, 'Day 22', '内容选自《变形记》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171222/vedio_8251513874005.mp3', '1:52', 112, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171222/1513874005875001.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 Metamorphosis（中文译《变形记》）</p><p>When Gregor Samsa woke one morning from troubled dreams, he found himself transformed right there in his bed into some sort of monstrous insect.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513874005, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', ''),
(450, 0, 'Day 23', '内容选自《局外人》', 'UploadFiles/vedio/20171223/vedio_9421513959452.mp3', '2:20', 140, '海海老师', 0.00, 'UploadFiles/product/20171223/1513959452224930.jpeg', '<p>本文选自 L''étranger（中文译《局外人》）</p><p>It was true. When she was at home, mother used to spend all her time just watching me in silence. She cried a lot the first few days at the old people''s home. But that was only because she wasn''t used to it.&nbsp;</p><p><br /></p>', 1513959452, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 2, '', '');
