(18, 0, 642, '关于of这个介词构成的短语,有时是从前面往后面翻译,有时又是从后面往前面翻译,有什么规律吗?', 1504256894, 0, 0, 1),
(19, 0, 759, 'And that’s why I never wrote a boy-meets-girl story for Collier’s. In a boy-meets-girl story the boy should always meet the girl. 为什么要加-这个号？？', 1504277122, 1, 0, 1),
(20, 0, 178, 'Now,there are two kinds of femme fetale. There is the femme fetale who is a femme fatale in every sense of the word, and there is the femme fatale who is not a femme fatale in every sense of the word.这个句子是什么意思', 1504334127, 0, 0, 1),
(21, 0, 21, 'North Korea’s official Korean Central News Agency issued a statement calling the exercise a “rash act of those taken aback” by North Korea’s recent missile launch.\n——rash act of those taken aback，这句话翻译为不计后果的举动，怎么理解的？aback是做为adv.吗？还是taken aback放在一起理解啊？', 1504434855, 0, 0, 1),
(22, 0, 337, 'turn out to be... 具体怎么理解呀？', 1504670581, 0, 0, 1),
(23, 0, 21, 'Cloud top temperatures in at the centre of the storm were near minus 83.5C (minus 117.7F), Nasa said.\n\n这句话为什么用in又用at？', 1504749098, 0, 0, 1),
(24, 0, 122, 'due to/ because/ cause by 都有因为...所以...，分别在什么情况下会选用其一？', 1504751436, 0, 0, 1),
(25, 0, 530, 'Of all the subjects on this planet, I think my parent would have been hard put to name one less useful than Greek mythology when it came to securing the keys to an executive bathroom. - J.K. Rowling 这句子读着不太顺，为什么是hard put to？是有什么语法在里面吗？Thx！', 1504765766, 0, 0, 1),
